window.BIBLE["Esther"] = {"1":{"chapter":"1","title":"VASHTI REMOVED","verses":{"1":{"text":"Now it came to pass in the days of Ahasuerus, (this is Ahasuerus which reigned, from India even unto Ethiopia, over an hundred and seven and twenty provinces:)","ref":"Esther 1:1","synthesized":"This is what happened in the days of Xerxes, who reigned over 127 provinces from India to Cush.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Now it came to pass in the days of Ahasuerus, (this is Ahasuerus which reigned, from India even unto Ethiopia, over an hundred and seven and twenty provinces:)"},"BSB":{"text":"This is what happened in the days of Xerxes, who reigned over 127 provinces from India to Cush."}},"definableWords":["days"],"peopleInVerse":["Cush"]},"2":{"text":"That in those days, when the king Ahasuerus sat on the throne of his kingdom, which was in Shushan the palace,","ref":"Esther 1:2","synthesized":"In those days King Xerxes sat on his royal throne in the citadel of Susa.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"That in those days, when the king Ahasuerus sat on the throne of his kingdom, which was in Shushan the palace,"},"BSB":{"text":"In those days King Xerxes sat on his royal throne in the citadel of Susa."}},"definableWords":["days","King","throne"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"3":{"text":"In the third year of his reign, he made a feast unto all his princes and his servants; the power of Persia and Media, the nobles and princes of the provinces, being before him:","ref":"Esther 1:3","synthesized":"In the third year of his reign, Xerxes held a feast for all his officials and servants. The military leaders of Persia and Media were there, along with the nobles and princes of the provinces.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"In the third year of his reign, he made a feast unto all his princes and his servants; the power of Persia and Media, the nobles and princes of the provinces, being before him:"},"BSB":{"text":"In the third year of his reign, Xerxes held a feast for all his officials and servants. The military leaders of Persia and Media were there, along with the nobles and princes of the provinces."}},"definableWords":["year","reign","servants"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"4":{"text":"When he shewed the riches of his glorious kingdom and the honour of his excellent majesty many days, even an hundred and fourscore days.","ref":"Esther 1:4","synthesized":"And for a full 180 days he displayed the glorious riches of his kingdom and the magnificent splendor of his greatness.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"When he shewed the riches of his glorious kingdom and the honour of his excellent majesty many days, even an hundred and fourscore days."},"BSB":{"text":"And for a full 180 days he displayed the glorious riches of his kingdom and the magnificent splendor of his greatness."}},"definableWords":["days","kingdom"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"5":{"text":"And when these days were expired, the king made a feast unto all the people that were present in Shushan the palace, both unto great and small, seven days, in the court of the garden of the king’s palace;","ref":"Esther 1:5","synthesized":"At the end of this time, in the garden court of the royal palace, the king held a seven-day feast for all the people in the citadel of Susa, from the least to the greatest.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And when these days were expired, the king made a feast unto all the people that were present in Shushan the palace, both unto great and small, seven days, in the court of the garden of the king’s palace;"},"BSB":{"text":"At the end of this time, in the garden court of the royal palace, the king held a seven-day feast for all the people in the citadel of Susa, from the least to the greatest."}},"definableWords":["garden","king","day","people"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"6":{"text":"Where were white, green, and blue, hangings, fastened with cords of fine linen and purple to silver rings and pillars of marble: the beds were of gold and silver, upon a pavement of red, and blue, and white, and black, marble.","ref":"Esther 1:6","synthesized":"Hangings of white and blue linen were fastened with cords of fine white and purple material to silver rings on the marble pillars. Gold and silver couches were arranged on a mosaic pavement of porphyry, marble, mother-of-pearl, and other costly stones.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Where were white, green, and blue, hangings, fastened with cords of fine linen and purple to silver rings and pillars of marble: the beds were of gold and silver, upon a pavement of red, and blue, and white, and black, marble."},"BSB":{"text":"Hangings of white and blue linen were fastened with cords of fine white and purple material to silver rings on the marble pillars. Gold and silver couches were arranged on a mosaic pavement of porphyry, marble, mother-of-pearl, and other costly stones."}},"definableWords":["mother"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"7":{"text":"And they gave them drink in vessels of gold, (the vessels being diverse one from another,) and royal wine in abundance, according to the state of the king.","ref":"Esther 1:7","synthesized":"Beverages were served in an array of goblets of gold, each with a different design, and the royal wine flowed freely, according to the king’s bounty.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And they gave them drink in vessels of gold, (the vessels being diverse one from another,) and royal wine in abundance, according to the state of the king."},"BSB":{"text":"Beverages were served in an array of goblets of gold, each with a different design, and the royal wine flowed freely, according to the king’s bounty."}},"definableWords":["king"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"8":{"text":"And the drinking was according to the law; none did compel: for so the king had appointed to all the officers of his house, that they should do according to every man’s pleasure.","ref":"Esther 1:8","synthesized":"By order of the king, no limit was placed on the drinking, and every official of his household was to serve each man whatever he desired.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And the drinking was according to the law; none did compel: for so the king had appointed to all the officers of his house, that they should do according to every man’s pleasure."},"BSB":{"text":"By order of the king, no limit was placed on the drinking, and every official of his household was to serve each man whatever he desired."}},"definableWords":["king","man"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"9":{"text":"Also Vashti the queen made a feast for the women in the royal house which belonged to king Ahasuerus.","ref":"Esther 1:9","synthesized":"Queen Vashti also gave a banquet for the women in the royal palace of King Xerxes.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Also Vashti the queen made a feast for the women in the royal house which belonged to king Ahasuerus."},"BSB":{"text":"Queen Vashti also gave a banquet for the women in the royal palace of King Xerxes."}},"definableWords":["women","King"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"10":{"text":"On the seventh day, when the heart of the king was merry with wine, he commanded Mehuman, Biztha, Harbona, Bigtha, and Abagtha, Zethar, and Carcas, the seven chamberlains that served in the presence of Ahasuerus the king,","ref":"Esther 1:10","synthesized":"On the seventh day, when the king’s heart was merry with wine, he ordered the seven eunuchs who served him—Mehuman, Biztha, Harbona, Bigtha, Abagtha, Zethar, and Carkas—","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"On the seventh day, when the heart of the king was merry with wine, he commanded Mehuman, Biztha, Harbona, Bigtha, and Abagtha, Zethar, and Carcas, the seven chamberlains that served in the presence of Ahasuerus the king,"},"BSB":{"text":"On the seventh day, when the king’s heart was merry with wine, he ordered the seven eunuchs who served him—Mehuman, Biztha, Harbona, Bigtha, Abagtha, Zethar, and Carkas—"}},"definableWords":["day","king","heart"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"11":{"text":"To bring Vashti the queen before the king with the crown royal, to shew the people and the princes her beauty: for she was fair to look on.","ref":"Esther 1:11","synthesized":"to bring Queen Vashti before him, wearing her royal crown, to display her beauty to the people and officials. For she was beautiful to behold.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"To bring Vashti the queen before the king with the crown royal, to shew the people and the princes her beauty: for she was fair to look on."},"BSB":{"text":"to bring Queen Vashti before him, wearing her royal crown, to display her beauty to the people and officials. For she was beautiful to behold."}},"definableWords":["crown","people"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"12":{"text":"But the queen Vashti refused to come at the king’s commandment by his chamberlains: therefore was the king very wroth, and his anger burned in him.","ref":"Esther 1:12","synthesized":"Queen Vashti, however, refused to come at the king’s command brought by his eunuchs. And the king became furious, and his anger burned within him.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"But the queen Vashti refused to come at the king’s commandment by his chamberlains: therefore was the king very wroth, and his anger burned in him."},"BSB":{"text":"Queen Vashti, however, refused to come at the king’s command brought by his eunuchs. And the king became furious, and his anger burned within him."}},"definableWords":["king","King","anger"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"13":{"text":"Then the king said to the wise men, which knew the times, (for so was the king’s manner toward all that knew law and judgment:","ref":"Esther 1:13","synthesized":"Then the king consulted the wise men who knew the times, for it was customary for him to confer with the experts in law and justice.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Then the king said to the wise men, which knew the times, (for so was the king’s manner toward all that knew law and judgment:"},"BSB":{"text":"Then the king consulted the wise men who knew the times, for it was customary for him to confer with the experts in law and justice."}},"definableWords":["king","men","law","justice"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"14":{"text":"And the next unto him was Carshena, Shethar, Admatha, Tarshish, Meres, Marsena, and Memucan, the seven princes of Persia and Media, which saw the king’s face, and which sat the first in the kingdom;)","ref":"Esther 1:14","synthesized":"His closest advisors were Carshena, Shethar, Admatha, Tarshish, Meres, Marsena, and Memucan, the seven princes of Persia and Media who had personal access to the king and ranked highest in the kingdom.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And the next unto him was Carshena, Shethar, Admatha, Tarshish, Meres, Marsena, and Memucan, the seven princes of Persia and Media, which saw the king’s face, and which sat the first in the kingdom;)"},"BSB":{"text":"His closest advisors were Carshena, Shethar, Admatha, Tarshish, Meres, Marsena, and Memucan, the seven princes of Persia and Media who had personal access to the king and ranked highest in the kingdom."}},"definableWords":["king","kingdom"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"15":{"text":"What shall we do unto the queen Vashti according to law, because she hath not performed the commandment of the king Ahasuerus by the chamberlains?","ref":"Esther 1:15","synthesized":"“According to law,” he asked, “what should be done with Queen Vashti, since she refused to obey the command of King Xerxes delivered by the eunuchs?”","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"What shall we do unto the queen Vashti according to law, because she hath not performed the commandment of the king Ahasuerus by the chamberlains?"},"BSB":{"text":"“According to law,” he asked, “what should be done with Queen Vashti, since she refused to obey the command of King Xerxes delivered by the eunuchs?”"}},"definableWords":["law","King"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"16":{"text":"And Memucan answered before the king and the princes, Vashti the queen hath not done wrong to the king only, but also to all the princes, and to all the people that are in all the provinces of the king Ahasuerus.","ref":"Esther 1:16","synthesized":"And in the presence of the king and his princes, Memucan replied, “Queen Vashti has wronged not only the king, but all the princes and the peoples in all the provinces of King Xerxes.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And Memucan answered before the king and the princes, Vashti the queen hath not done wrong to the king only, but also to all the princes, and to all the people that are in all the provinces of the king Ahasuerus."},"BSB":{"text":"And in the presence of the king and his princes, Memucan replied, “Queen Vashti has wronged not only the king, but all the princes and the peoples in all the provinces of King Xerxes."}},"definableWords":["king","King"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"17":{"text":"For this deed of the queen shall come abroad unto all women, so that they shall despise their husbands in their eyes, when it shall be reported, The king Ahasuerus commanded Vashti the queen to be brought in before him, but she came not.","ref":"Esther 1:17","synthesized":"For the conduct of the queen will become known to all women, causing them to despise their husbands and say, ‘King Xerxes ordered Queen Vashti to be brought before him, but she did not come.’","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"For this deed of the queen shall come abroad unto all women, so that they shall despise their husbands in their eyes, when it shall be reported, The king Ahasuerus commanded Vashti the queen to be brought in before him, but she came not."},"BSB":{"text":"For the conduct of the queen will become known to all women, causing them to despise their husbands and say, ‘King Xerxes ordered Queen Vashti to be brought before him, but she did not come.’"}},"definableWords":["women","King"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"18":{"text":"Likewise shall the ladies of Persia and Media say this day unto all the king’s princes, which have heard of the deed of the queen. Thus shall there arise too much contempt and wrath.","ref":"Esther 1:18","synthesized":"This very day the noble women of Persia and Media who have heard about the queen’s conduct will say the same thing to all the king’s officials, resulting in much contempt and wrath.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Likewise shall the ladies of Persia and Media say this day unto all the king’s princes, which have heard of the deed of the queen. Thus shall there arise too much contempt and wrath."},"BSB":{"text":"This very day the noble women of Persia and Media who have heard about the queen’s conduct will say the same thing to all the king’s officials, resulting in much contempt and wrath."}},"definableWords":["day","women","king","wrath"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"19":{"text":"If it please the king, let there go a royal commandment from him, and let it be written among the laws of the Persians and the Medes, that it be not altered, That Vashti come no more before king Ahasuerus; and let the king give her royal estate unto another that is better than she.","ref":"Esther 1:19","synthesized":"So if it pleases the king, let him issue a royal decree, and let it be recorded in the laws of Persia and Media so that it cannot be repealed, that Vashti shall never again enter the presence of King Xerxes, and that her royal position shall be given to a woman better than she.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"If it please the king, let there go a royal commandment from him, and let it be written among the laws of the Persians and the Medes, that it be not altered, That Vashti come no more before king Ahasuerus; and let the king give her royal estate unto another that is better than she."},"BSB":{"text":"So if it pleases the king, let him issue a royal decree, and let it be recorded in the laws of Persia and Media so that it cannot be repealed, that Vashti shall never again enter the presence of King Xerxes, and that her royal position shall be given to a woman better than she."}},"definableWords":["king","King","woman"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"20":{"text":"And when the king’s decree which he shall make shall be published throughout all his empire, (for it is great,) all the wives shall give to their husbands honour, both to great and small.","ref":"Esther 1:20","synthesized":"The edict the king issues will be heard throughout his vast kingdom—and so all women, from the least to the greatest, will honor their husbands.”","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And when the king’s decree which he shall make shall be published throughout all his empire, (for it is great,) all the wives shall give to their husbands honour, both to great and small."},"BSB":{"text":"The edict the king issues will be heard throughout his vast kingdom—and so all women, from the least to the greatest, will honor their husbands.”"}},"definableWords":["king","kingdom","women"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"21":{"text":"And the saying pleased the king and the princes; and the king did according to the word of Memucan:","ref":"Esther 1:21","synthesized":"The king and his princes were pleased with this counsel; so the king did as Memucan had advised.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And the saying pleased the king and the princes; and the king did according to the word of Memucan:"},"BSB":{"text":"The king and his princes were pleased with this counsel; so the king did as Memucan had advised."}},"definableWords":["king","King"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"22":{"text":"For he sent letters into all the king’s provinces, into every province according to the writing thereof, and to every people after their language, that every man should bear rule in his own house, and that it should be published according to the language of every people.","ref":"Esther 1:22","synthesized":"He sent letters to all the provinces of the kingdom, to each province in its own script and to each people in their own language, proclaiming that every man should be master of his own household.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"For he sent letters into all the king’s provinces, into every province according to the writing thereof, and to every people after their language, that every man should bear rule in his own house, and that it should be published according to the language of every people."},"BSB":{"text":"He sent letters to all the provinces of the kingdom, to each province in its own script and to each people in their own language, proclaiming that every man should be master of his own household."}},"definableWords":["kingdom","people","man"],"peopleInVerse":[]}}},"2":{"chapter":"2","title":"ESTHER BECOMES QUEEN","verses":{"1":{"text":"After these things, when the wrath of king Ahasuerus was appeased, he remembered Vashti, and what she had done, and what was decreed against her.","ref":"Esther 2:1","synthesized":"Some time later, when the anger of King Xerxes had subsided, he remembered Vashti and what she had done, and what had been decreed against her.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"After these things, when the wrath of king Ahasuerus was appeased, he remembered Vashti, and what she had done, and what was decreed against her."},"BSB":{"text":"Some time later, when the anger of King Xerxes had subsided, he remembered Vashti and what she had done, and what had been decreed against her."}},"definableWords":["anger","King","remembered"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"2":{"text":"Then said the king’s servants that ministered unto him, Let there be fair young virgins sought for the king:","ref":"Esther 2:2","synthesized":"Then the king’s attendants proposed, “Let a search be made for beautiful young virgins for the king,","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Then said the king’s servants that ministered unto him, Let there be fair young virgins sought for the king:"},"BSB":{"text":"Then the king’s attendants proposed, “Let a search be made for beautiful young virgins for the king,"}},"definableWords":["king","made","King"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"3":{"text":"And let the king appoint officers in all the provinces of his kingdom, that they may gather together all the fair young virgins unto Shushan the palace, to the house of the women, unto the custody of Hege the king’s chamberlain, keeper of the women; and let their things for purification be given them:","ref":"Esther 2:3","synthesized":"and let the king appoint commissioners in each province of his kingdom to assemble all the beautiful young women into the harem at the citadel of Susa. Let them be placed under the care of Hegai, the king’s eunuch in charge of the women, and let them be given beauty treatments.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And let the king appoint officers in all the provinces of his kingdom, that they may gather together all the fair young virgins unto Shushan the palace, to the house of the women, unto the custody of Hege the king’s chamberlain, keeper of the women; and let their things for purification be given them:"},"BSB":{"text":"and let the king appoint commissioners in each province of his kingdom to assemble all the beautiful young women into the harem at the citadel of Susa. Let them be placed under the care of Hegai, the king’s eunuch in charge of the women, and let them be given beauty treatments."}},"definableWords":["king","kingdom","women","King","charge"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"4":{"text":"And let the maiden which pleaseth the king be queen instead of Vashti. And the thing pleased the king; and he did so.","ref":"Esther 2:4","synthesized":"Then let the young woman who pleases the king become queen in place of Vashti.”  This suggestion pleased the king, and he acted accordingly.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And let the maiden which pleaseth the king be queen instead of Vashti. And the thing pleased the king; and he did so."},"BSB":{"text":"Then let the young woman who pleases the king become queen in place of Vashti.”  This suggestion pleased the king, and he acted accordingly."}},"definableWords":["woman","king","King"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"5":{"text":"Now in Shushan the palace there was a certain Jew, whose name was Mordecai, the son of Jair, the son of Shimei, the son of Kish, a Benjamite;","ref":"Esther 2:5","synthesized":"Now there was at the citadel of Susa a Jewish man from the tribe of Benjamin named Mordecai son of Jair, the son of Shimei, the son of Kish.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Now in Shushan the palace there was a certain Jew, whose name was Mordecai, the son of Jair, the son of Shimei, the son of Kish, a Benjamite;"},"BSB":{"text":"Now there was at the citadel of Susa a Jewish man from the tribe of Benjamin named Mordecai son of Jair, the son of Shimei, the son of Kish."}},"definableWords":["man","tribe","Benjamin","son","Son"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"6":{"text":"Who had been carried away from Jerusalem with the captivity which had been carried away with Jeconiah king of Judah, whom Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon had carried away.","ref":"Esther 2:6","synthesized":"He had been carried into exile from Jerusalem by Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon among those taken captive with Jeconiah king of Judah.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Who had been carried away from Jerusalem with the captivity which had been carried away with Jeconiah king of Judah, whom Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon had carried away."},"BSB":{"text":"He had been carried into exile from Jerusalem by Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon among those taken captive with Jeconiah king of Judah."}},"definableWords":["Jerusalem","king","Babylon","King","Judah"],"peopleInVerse":["Nebuchadnezzar"]},"7":{"text":"And he brought up Hadassah, that is, Esther, his uncle’s daughter: for she had neither father nor mother, and the maid was fair and beautiful; whom Mordecai, when her father and mother were dead, took for his own daughter.","ref":"Esther 2:7","synthesized":"And Mordecai had brought up Hadassah (that is, Esther), the daughter of his uncle, because she did not have a father or mother. The young woman was lovely in form and appearance, and when her father and mother had died, Mordecai had taken her in as his own daughter.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And he brought up Hadassah, that is, Esther, his uncle’s daughter: for she had neither father nor mother, and the maid was fair and beautiful; whom Mordecai, when her father and mother were dead, took for his own daughter."},"BSB":{"text":"And Mordecai had brought up Hadassah (that is, Esther), the daughter of his uncle, because she did not have a father or mother. The young woman was lovely in form and appearance, and when her father and mother had died, Mordecai had taken her in as his own daughter."}},"definableWords":["daughter","father","or","mother","woman","form","Father"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"8":{"text":"So it came to pass, when the king’s commandment and his decree was heard, and when many maidens were gathered together unto Shushan the palace, to the custody of Hegai, that Esther was brought also unto the king’s house, to the custody of Hegai, keeper of the women.","ref":"Esther 2:8","synthesized":"When the king’s command and edict had been proclaimed, many young women gathered at the citadel of Susa under the care of Hegai. Esther was also taken to the palace and placed under the care of Hegai, the custodian of the women.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"So it came to pass, when the king’s commandment and his decree was heard, and when many maidens were gathered together unto Shushan the palace, to the custody of Hegai, that Esther was brought also unto the king’s house, to the custody of Hegai, keeper of the women."},"BSB":{"text":"When the king’s command and edict had been proclaimed, many young women gathered at the citadel of Susa under the care of Hegai. Esther was also taken to the palace and placed under the care of Hegai, the custodian of the women."}},"definableWords":["king","women"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"9":{"text":"And the maiden pleased him, and she obtained kindness of him; and he speedily gave her her things for purification, with such things as belonged to her, and seven maidens, which were meet to be given her, out of the king’s house: and he preferred her and her maids unto the best place of the house of the women.","ref":"Esther 2:9","synthesized":"And the young woman pleased him and obtained his favor, so he quickly provided her with beauty treatments and the special diet. He assigned to her seven select maidservants from the palace and transferred her with them to the best place in the harem.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And the maiden pleased him, and she obtained kindness of him; and he speedily gave her her things for purification, with such things as belonged to her, and seven maidens, which were meet to be given her, out of the king’s house: and he preferred her and her maids unto the best place of the house of the women."},"BSB":{"text":"And the young woman pleased him and obtained his favor, so he quickly provided her with beauty treatments and the special diet. He assigned to her seven select maidservants from the palace and transferred her with them to the best place in the harem."}},"definableWords":["woman"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"10":{"text":"Esther had not shewed her people nor her kindred: for Mordecai had charged her that she should not shew it.","ref":"Esther 2:10","synthesized":"Esther did not reveal her people or her lineage, because Mordecai had instructed her not to do so.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Esther had not shewed her people nor her kindred: for Mordecai had charged her that she should not shew it."},"BSB":{"text":"Esther did not reveal her people or her lineage, because Mordecai had instructed her not to do so."}},"definableWords":["people","or"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"11":{"text":"And Mordecai walked every day before the court of the women’s house, to know how Esther did, and what should become of her.","ref":"Esther 2:11","synthesized":"And every day Mordecai would walk back and forth in front of the court of the harem to learn about Esther’s welfare and what was happening to her.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And Mordecai walked every day before the court of the women’s house, to know how Esther did, and what should become of her."},"BSB":{"text":"And every day Mordecai would walk back and forth in front of the court of the harem to learn about Esther’s welfare and what was happening to her."}},"definableWords":["day","walk"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"12":{"text":"Now when every maid’s turn was come to go in to king Ahasuerus, after that she had been twelve months, according to the manner of the women, (for so were the days of their purifications accomplished, to wit, six months with oil of myrrh, and six months with sweet odours, and with other things for the purifying of the women;)","ref":"Esther 2:12","synthesized":"In the twelve months before her turn to go to King Xerxes, the harem regulation required each young woman to receive beauty treatments with oil of myrrh for six months, and then with perfumes and cosmetics for another six months.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Now when every maid’s turn was come to go in to king Ahasuerus, after that she had been twelve months, according to the manner of the women, (for so were the days of their purifications accomplished, to wit, six months with oil of myrrh, and six months with sweet odours, and with other things for the purifying of the women;)"},"BSB":{"text":"In the twelve months before her turn to go to King Xerxes, the harem regulation required each young woman to receive beauty treatments with oil of myrrh for six months, and then with perfumes and cosmetics for another six months."}},"definableWords":["King","woman"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"13":{"text":"Then thus came every maiden unto the king; whatsoever she desired was given her to go with her out of the house of the women unto the king’s house.","ref":"Esther 2:13","synthesized":"When the young woman would go to the king, she was given whatever she requested to take with her from the harem to the king’s palace.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Then thus came every maiden unto the king; whatsoever she desired was given her to go with her out of the house of the women unto the king’s house."},"BSB":{"text":"When the young woman would go to the king, she was given whatever she requested to take with her from the harem to the king’s palace."}},"definableWords":["woman","king","King"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"14":{"text":"In the evening she went, and on the morrow she returned into the second house of the women, to the custody of Shaashgaz, the king’s chamberlain, which kept the concubines: she came in unto the king no more, except the king delighted in her, and that she were called by name.","ref":"Esther 2:14","synthesized":"She would go there in the evening, and in the morning she would return to a second harem under the care of Shaashgaz, the king’s eunuch in charge of the concubines. She would not return to the king unless he delighted in her and summoned her by name.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"In the evening she went, and on the morrow she returned into the second house of the women, to the custody of Shaashgaz, the king’s chamberlain, which kept the concubines: she came in unto the king no more, except the king delighted in her, and that she were called by name."},"BSB":{"text":"She would go there in the evening, and in the morning she would return to a second harem under the care of Shaashgaz, the king’s eunuch in charge of the concubines. She would not return to the king unless he delighted in her and summoned her by name."}},"definableWords":["king","charge","King","name"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"15":{"text":"Now when the turn of Esther, the daughter of Abihail the uncle of Mordecai, who had taken her for his daughter, was come to go in unto the king, she required nothing but what Hegai the king’s chamberlain, the keeper of the women, appointed. And Esther obtained favour in the sight of all them that looked upon her.","ref":"Esther 2:15","synthesized":"Now Esther was the daughter of Abihail, the uncle from whom Mordecai had adopted her as his own daughter. And when it was her turn to go to the king, she did not ask for anything except what Hegai, the king’s trusted official in charge of the harem, had advised. And Esther found favor in the eyes of everyone who saw her.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Now when the turn of Esther, the daughter of Abihail the uncle of Mordecai, who had taken her for his daughter, was come to go in unto the king, she required nothing but what Hegai the king’s chamberlain, the keeper of the women, appointed. And Esther obtained favour in the sight of all them that looked upon her."},"BSB":{"text":"Now Esther was the daughter of Abihail, the uncle from whom Mordecai had adopted her as his own daughter. And when it was her turn to go to the king, she did not ask for anything except what Hegai, the king’s trusted official in charge of the harem, had advised. And Esther found favor in the eyes of everyone who saw her."}},"definableWords":["daughter","king","King","charge","saw"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"16":{"text":"So Esther was taken unto king Ahasuerus into his house royal in the tenth month, which is the month Tebeth, in the seventh year of his reign.","ref":"Esther 2:16","synthesized":"She was taken to King Xerxes in the royal palace in the tenth month, the month of Tebeth, in the seventh year of his reign.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"So Esther was taken unto king Ahasuerus into his house royal in the tenth month, which is the month Tebeth, in the seventh year of his reign."},"BSB":{"text":"She was taken to King Xerxes in the royal palace in the tenth month, the month of Tebeth, in the seventh year of his reign."}},"definableWords":["King","year","reign"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"17":{"text":"And the king loved Esther above all the women, and she obtained grace and favour in his sight more than all the virgins; so that he set the royal crown upon her head, and made her queen instead of Vashti.","ref":"Esther 2:17","synthesized":"And the king loved Esther more than all the other women, and she found grace and favor in his sight more than all of the other virgins. So he placed the royal crown upon her head and made her queen in place of Vashti.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And the king loved Esther above all the women, and she obtained grace and favour in his sight more than all the virgins; so that he set the royal crown upon her head, and made her queen instead of Vashti."},"BSB":{"text":"And the king loved Esther more than all the other women, and she found grace and favor in his sight more than all of the other virgins. So he placed the royal crown upon her head and made her queen in place of Vashti."}},"definableWords":["king","women","grace","crown","made"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"18":{"text":"Then the king made a great feast unto all his princes and his servants, even Esther’s feast; and he made a release to the provinces, and gave gifts, according to the state of the king.","ref":"Esther 2:18","synthesized":"Then the king held a great banquet, Esther’s banquet, for all his officials and servants. He proclaimed a tax holiday in the provinces and gave gifts worthy of the king’s bounty.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Then the king made a great feast unto all his princes and his servants, even Esther’s feast; and he made a release to the provinces, and gave gifts, according to the state of the king."},"BSB":{"text":"Then the king held a great banquet, Esther’s banquet, for all his officials and servants. He proclaimed a tax holiday in the provinces and gave gifts worthy of the king’s bounty."}},"definableWords":["king","great","servants","King"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"19":{"text":"And when the virgins were gathered together the second time, then Mordecai sat in the king’s gate.","ref":"Esther 2:19","synthesized":"When the virgins were assembled a second time, Mordecai was sitting at the king’s gate.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And when the virgins were gathered together the second time, then Mordecai sat in the king’s gate."},"BSB":{"text":"When the virgins were assembled a second time, Mordecai was sitting at the king’s gate."}},"definableWords":["king"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"20":{"text":"Esther had not yet shewed her kindred nor her people; as Mordecai had charged her: for Esther did the commandment of Mordecai, like as when she was brought up with him.","ref":"Esther 2:20","synthesized":"Esther still had not revealed her lineage or her people, just as Mordecai had instructed. She obeyed Mordecai’s command, as she had done under his care.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Esther had not yet shewed her kindred nor her people; as Mordecai had charged her: for Esther did the commandment of Mordecai, like as when she was brought up with him."},"BSB":{"text":"Esther still had not revealed her lineage or her people, just as Mordecai had instructed. She obeyed Mordecai’s command, as she had done under his care."}},"definableWords":["or","people"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"21":{"text":"In those days, while Mordecai sat in the king’s gate, two of the king’s chamberlains, Bigthan and Teresh, of those which kept the door, were wroth, and sought to lay hand on the king Ahasuerus.","ref":"Esther 2:21","synthesized":"In those days, while Mordecai was sitting at the king’s gate, Bigthan and Teresh, two of the king’s eunuchs who guarded the entrance, grew angry and conspired to assassinate King Xerxes.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"In those days, while Mordecai sat in the king’s gate, two of the king’s chamberlains, Bigthan and Teresh, of those which kept the door, were wroth, and sought to lay hand on the king Ahasuerus."},"BSB":{"text":"In those days, while Mordecai was sitting at the king’s gate, Bigthan and Teresh, two of the king’s eunuchs who guarded the entrance, grew angry and conspired to assassinate King Xerxes."}},"definableWords":["days","king","King"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"22":{"text":"And the thing was known to Mordecai, who told it unto Esther the queen; and Esther certified the king thereof in Mordecai’s name.","ref":"Esther 2:22","synthesized":"When Mordecai learned of the plot, he reported it to Queen Esther, and she informed the king on Mordecai’s behalf.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And the thing was known to Mordecai, who told it unto Esther the queen; and Esther certified the king thereof in Mordecai’s name."},"BSB":{"text":"When Mordecai learned of the plot, he reported it to Queen Esther, and she informed the king on Mordecai’s behalf."}},"definableWords":["king"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"23":{"text":"And when inquisition was made of the matter, it was found out; therefore they were both hanged on a tree: and it was written in the book of the chronicles before the king.","ref":"Esther 2:23","synthesized":"After the report had been investigated and verified, both officials were hanged on the gallows. And all this was recorded in the Book of the Chronicles in the presence of the king.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And when inquisition was made of the matter, it was found out; therefore they were both hanged on a tree: and it was written in the book of the chronicles before the king."},"BSB":{"text":"After the report had been investigated and verified, both officials were hanged on the gallows. And all this was recorded in the Book of the Chronicles in the presence of the king."}},"definableWords":["king"],"peopleInVerse":[]}}},"3":{"chapter":"3","title":"HAMAN'S PLOT AGAINST THE JEWS","verses":{"1":{"text":"After these things did king Ahasuerus promote Haman the son of Hammedatha the Agagite, and advanced him, and set his seat above all the princes that were with him.","ref":"Esther 3:1","synthesized":"After these events, King Xerxes honored Haman son of Hammedatha, the Agagite, elevating him to a position above all the princes who were with him.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"After these things did king Ahasuerus promote Haman the son of Hammedatha the Agagite, and advanced him, and set his seat above all the princes that were with him."},"BSB":{"text":"After these events, King Xerxes honored Haman son of Hammedatha, the Agagite, elevating him to a position above all the princes who were with him."}},"definableWords":["King","son"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"2":{"text":"And all the king’s servants, that were in the king’s gate, bowed, and reverenced Haman: for the king had so commanded concerning him. But Mordecai bowed not, nor did him reverence.","ref":"Esther 3:2","synthesized":"All the royal servants at the king’s gate bowed down and paid homage to Haman, because the king had commanded that this be done for him. But Mordecai would not bow down or pay homage.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And all the king’s servants, that were in the king’s gate, bowed, and reverenced Haman: for the king had so commanded concerning him. But Mordecai bowed not, nor did him reverence."},"BSB":{"text":"All the royal servants at the king’s gate bowed down and paid homage to Haman, because the king had commanded that this be done for him. But Mordecai would not bow down or pay homage."}},"definableWords":["servants","king","King","or"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"3":{"text":"Then the king’s servants, which were in the king’s gate, said unto Mordecai, Why transgressest thou the king’s commandment?","ref":"Esther 3:3","synthesized":"Then the royal servants at the king’s gate asked Mordecai, “Why do you disobey the command of the king?”","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Then the king’s servants, which were in the king’s gate, said unto Mordecai, Why transgressest thou the king’s commandment?"},"BSB":{"text":"Then the royal servants at the king’s gate asked Mordecai, “Why do you disobey the command of the king?”"}},"definableWords":["servants","king","King"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"4":{"text":"Now it came to pass, when they spake daily unto him, and he hearkened not unto them, that they told Haman, to see whether Mordecai’s matters would stand: for he had told them that he was a Jew.","ref":"Esther 3:4","synthesized":"Day after day they warned him, but he would not comply. So they reported it to Haman to see whether Mordecai’s behavior would be tolerated, since he had told them he was a Jew.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Now it came to pass, when they spake daily unto him, and he hearkened not unto them, that they told Haman, to see whether Mordecai’s matters would stand: for he had told them that he was a Jew."},"BSB":{"text":"Day after day they warned him, but he would not comply. So they reported it to Haman to see whether Mordecai’s behavior would be tolerated, since he had told them he was a Jew."}},"definableWords":["day","see","Jew"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"5":{"text":"And when Haman saw that Mordecai bowed not, nor did him reverence, then was Haman full of wrath.","ref":"Esther 3:5","synthesized":"When Haman saw that Mordecai would not bow down or pay him homage, he was filled with rage.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And when Haman saw that Mordecai bowed not, nor did him reverence, then was Haman full of wrath."},"BSB":{"text":"When Haman saw that Mordecai would not bow down or pay him homage, he was filled with rage."}},"definableWords":["saw","or"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"6":{"text":"And he thought scorn to lay hands on Mordecai alone; for they had shewed him the people of Mordecai: wherefore Haman sought to destroy all the Jews that were throughout the whole kingdom of Ahasuerus, even the people of Mordecai.","ref":"Esther 3:6","synthesized":"And when he learned the identity of Mordecai’s people, he scorned the notion of laying hands on Mordecai alone. Instead, he sought to destroy all of Mordecai’s people, the Jews, throughout the kingdom of Xerxes.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And he thought scorn to lay hands on Mordecai alone; for they had shewed him the people of Mordecai: wherefore Haman sought to destroy all the Jews that were throughout the whole kingdom of Ahasuerus, even the people of Mordecai."},"BSB":{"text":"And when he learned the identity of Mordecai’s people, he scorned the notion of laying hands on Mordecai alone. Instead, he sought to destroy all of Mordecai’s people, the Jews, throughout the kingdom of Xerxes."}},"definableWords":["people","kingdom"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"7":{"text":"In the first month, that is, the month Nisan, in the twelfth year of king Ahasuerus, they cast Pur, that is, the lot, before Haman from day to day, and from month to month, to the twelfth month, that is, the month Adar.","ref":"Esther 3:7","synthesized":"In the twelfth year of King Xerxes, in the first month, the month of Nisan, the Pur (that is, the lot) was cast before Haman to determine a day and month. And the lot fell on the twelfth month, the month of Adar.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"In the first month, that is, the month Nisan, in the twelfth year of king Ahasuerus, they cast Pur, that is, the lot, before Haman from day to day, and from month to month, to the twelfth month, that is, the month Adar."},"BSB":{"text":"In the twelfth year of King Xerxes, in the first month, the month of Nisan, the Pur (that is, the lot) was cast before Haman to determine a day and month. And the lot fell on the twelfth month, the month of Adar."}},"definableWords":["year","King","Lot","day"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"8":{"text":"And Haman said unto king Ahasuerus, There is a certain people scattered abroad and dispersed among the people in all the provinces of thy kingdom; and their laws are diverse from all people; neither keep they the king’s laws: therefore it is not for the king’s profit to suffer them.","ref":"Esther 3:8","synthesized":"Then Haman informed King Xerxes, “There is a certain people scattered and dispersed among the peoples of every province of your kingdom. Their laws are different from everyone else’s, and they do not obey the king’s laws. So it is not in the king’s best interest to tolerate them.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And Haman said unto king Ahasuerus, There is a certain people scattered abroad and dispersed among the people in all the provinces of thy kingdom; and their laws are diverse from all people; neither keep they the king’s laws: therefore it is not for the king’s profit to suffer them."},"BSB":{"text":"Then Haman informed King Xerxes, “There is a certain people scattered and dispersed among the peoples of every province of your kingdom. Their laws are different from everyone else’s, and they do not obey the king’s laws. So it is not in the king’s best interest to tolerate them."}},"definableWords":["King","people","kingdom","king"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"9":{"text":"If it please the king, let it be written that they may be destroyed: and I will pay ten thousand talents of silver to the hands of those that have the charge of the business, to bring it into the king’s treasuries.","ref":"Esther 3:9","synthesized":"If it pleases the king, let a decree be issued to destroy them, and I will deposit ten thousand talents of silver into the royal treasury to pay those who carry it out.”","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"If it please the king, let it be written that they may be destroyed: and I will pay ten thousand talents of silver to the hands of those that have the charge of the business, to bring it into the king’s treasuries."},"BSB":{"text":"If it pleases the king, let a decree be issued to destroy them, and I will deposit ten thousand talents of silver into the royal treasury to pay those who carry it out.”"}},"definableWords":["king"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"10":{"text":"And the king took his ring from his hand, and gave it unto Haman the son of Hammedatha the Agagite, the Jews’ enemy.","ref":"Esther 3:10","synthesized":"So the king removed the signet ring from his finger and gave it to Haman son of Hammedatha, the Agagite, the enemy of the Jews.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And the king took his ring from his hand, and gave it unto Haman the son of Hammedatha the Agagite, the Jews’ enemy."},"BSB":{"text":"So the king removed the signet ring from his finger and gave it to Haman son of Hammedatha, the Agagite, the enemy of the Jews."}},"definableWords":["king","son"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"11":{"text":"And the king said unto Haman, The silver is given to thee, the people also, to do with them as it seemeth good to thee.","ref":"Esther 3:11","synthesized":"“Keep your money,” said the king to Haman. “These people are given to you to do with them as you please.”","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And the king said unto Haman, The silver is given to thee, the people also, to do with them as it seemeth good to thee."},"BSB":{"text":"“Keep your money,” said the king to Haman. “These people are given to you to do with them as you please.”"}},"definableWords":["keep","king","people"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"12":{"text":"Then were the king’s scribes called on the thirteenth day of the first month, and there was written according to all that Haman had commanded unto the king’s lieutenants, and to the governors that were over every province, and to the rulers of every people of every province according to the writing thereof, and to every people after their language; in the name of king Ahasuerus was it written, and sealed with the king’s ring.","ref":"Esther 3:12","synthesized":"On the thirteenth day of the first month, the royal scribes were summoned and the order was written exactly as Haman commanded the royal satraps, the governors of each province, and the officials of each people, in the script of each province and the language of every people. It was written in the name of King Xerxes and sealed with the royal signet ring.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Then were the king’s scribes called on the thirteenth day of the first month, and there was written according to all that Haman had commanded unto the king’s lieutenants, and to the governors that were over every province, and to the rulers of every people of every province according to the writing thereof, and to every people after their language; in the name of king Ahasuerus was it written, and sealed with the king’s ring."},"BSB":{"text":"On the thirteenth day of the first month, the royal scribes were summoned and the order was written exactly as Haman commanded the royal satraps, the governors of each province, and the officials of each people, in the script of each province and the language of every people. It was written in the name of King Xerxes and sealed with the royal signet ring."}},"definableWords":["day","people","name","King"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"13":{"text":"And the letters were sent by posts into all the king’s provinces, to destroy, to kill, and to cause to perish, all Jews, both young and old, little children and women, in one day, even upon the thirteenth day of the twelfth month, which is the month Adar, and to take the spoil of them for a prey.","ref":"Esther 3:13","synthesized":"And the letters were sent by couriers to each of the royal provinces with the order to destroy, kill, and annihilate all the Jews—young and old, women and children—and to plunder their possessions on a single day, the thirteenth day of Adar, the twelfth month.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And the letters were sent by posts into all the king’s provinces, to destroy, to kill, and to cause to perish, all Jews, both young and old, little children and women, in one day, even upon the thirteenth day of the twelfth month, which is the month Adar, and to take the spoil of them for a prey."},"BSB":{"text":"And the letters were sent by couriers to each of the royal provinces with the order to destroy, kill, and annihilate all the Jews—young and old, women and children—and to plunder their possessions on a single day, the thirteenth day of Adar, the twelfth month."}},"definableWords":["women","day"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"14":{"text":"The copy of the writing for a commandment to be given in every province was published unto all people, that they should be ready against that day.","ref":"Esther 3:14","synthesized":"A copy of the text of the edict was to be issued in every province and published to all the people, so that they would be ready on that day.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"The copy of the writing for a commandment to be given in every province was published unto all people, that they should be ready against that day."},"BSB":{"text":"A copy of the text of the edict was to be issued in every province and published to all the people, so that they would be ready on that day."}},"definableWords":["people","day"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"15":{"text":"The posts went out, being hastened by the king’s commandment, and the decree was given in Shushan the palace. And the king and Haman sat down to drink; but the city Shushan was perplexed.","ref":"Esther 3:15","synthesized":"The couriers left, spurred on by the king’s command, and the edict was issued in the citadel of Susa. Then the king and Haman sat down to drink, but the city of Susa was in confusion.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"The posts went out, being hastened by the king’s commandment, and the decree was given in Shushan the palace. And the king and Haman sat down to drink; but the city Shushan was perplexed."},"BSB":{"text":"The couriers left, spurred on by the king’s command, and the edict was issued in the citadel of Susa. Then the king and Haman sat down to drink, but the city of Susa was in confusion."}},"definableWords":["king","King"],"peopleInVerse":[]}}},"4":{"chapter":"4","title":"FOR SUCH A TIME AS THIS","verses":{"1":{"text":"When Mordecai perceived all that was done, Mordecai rent his clothes, and put on sackcloth with ashes, and went out into the midst of the city, and cried with a loud and a bitter cry;","ref":"Esther 4:1","synthesized":"When Mordecai learned of all that had happened, he tore his clothes, put on sackcloth and ashes, and went out into the middle of the city, wailing loudly and bitterly.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"When Mordecai perceived all that was done, Mordecai rent his clothes, and put on sackcloth with ashes, and went out into the midst of the city, and cried with a loud and a bitter cry;"},"BSB":{"text":"When Mordecai learned of all that had happened, he tore his clothes, put on sackcloth and ashes, and went out into the middle of the city, wailing loudly and bitterly."}},"definableWords":[],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"2":{"text":"And came even before the king’s gate: for none might enter into the king’s gate clothed with sackcloth.","ref":"Esther 4:2","synthesized":"But he went only as far as the king’s gate, because the law prohibited anyone wearing sackcloth from entering that gate.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And came even before the king’s gate: for none might enter into the king’s gate clothed with sackcloth."},"BSB":{"text":"But he went only as far as the king’s gate, because the law prohibited anyone wearing sackcloth from entering that gate."}},"definableWords":["king","law"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"3":{"text":"And in every province, whithersoever the king’s commandment and his decree came, there was great mourning among the Jews, and fasting, and weeping, and wailing; and many lay in sackcloth and ashes.","ref":"Esther 4:3","synthesized":"In every province to which the king’s command and edict came, there was great mourning among the Jews. They fasted, wept, and lamented, and many lay in sackcloth and ashes.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And in every province, whithersoever the king’s commandment and his decree came, there was great mourning among the Jews, and fasting, and weeping, and wailing; and many lay in sackcloth and ashes."},"BSB":{"text":"In every province to which the king’s command and edict came, there was great mourning among the Jews. They fasted, wept, and lamented, and many lay in sackcloth and ashes."}},"definableWords":["king","great"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"4":{"text":"So Esther’s maids and her chamberlains came and told it her. Then was the queen exceedingly grieved; and she sent raiment to clothe Mordecai, and to take away his sackcloth from him: but he received it not.","ref":"Esther 4:4","synthesized":"When Esther’s maidens and eunuchs came and told her about Mordecai, the queen was overcome with distress. She sent clothes for Mordecai to wear instead of his sackcloth, but he would not accept them.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"So Esther’s maids and her chamberlains came and told it her. Then was the queen exceedingly grieved; and she sent raiment to clothe Mordecai, and to take away his sackcloth from him: but he received it not."},"BSB":{"text":"When Esther’s maidens and eunuchs came and told her about Mordecai, the queen was overcome with distress. She sent clothes for Mordecai to wear instead of his sackcloth, but he would not accept them."}},"definableWords":["overcome"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"5":{"text":"Then called Esther for Hatach, one of the king’s chamberlains, whom he had appointed to attend upon her, and gave him a commandment to Mordecai, to know what it was, and why it was.","ref":"Esther 4:5","synthesized":"Then Esther summoned Hathach, one of the king’s eunuchs appointed to her, and she dispatched him to Mordecai to learn what was troubling him and why.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Then called Esther for Hatach, one of the king’s chamberlains, whom he had appointed to attend upon her, and gave him a commandment to Mordecai, to know what it was, and why it was."},"BSB":{"text":"Then Esther summoned Hathach, one of the king’s eunuchs appointed to her, and she dispatched him to Mordecai to learn what was troubling him and why."}},"definableWords":["one","king"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"6":{"text":"So Hatach went forth to Mordecai unto the street of the city, which was before the king’s gate.","ref":"Esther 4:6","synthesized":"So Hathach went out to Mordecai in the city square in front of the king’s gate,","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"So Hatach went forth to Mordecai unto the street of the city, which was before the king’s gate."},"BSB":{"text":"So Hathach went out to Mordecai in the city square in front of the king’s gate,"}},"definableWords":["king"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"7":{"text":"And Mordecai told him of all that had happened unto him, and of the sum of the money that Haman had promised to pay to the king’s treasuries for the Jews, to destroy them.","ref":"Esther 4:7","synthesized":"and Mordecai told him all that had happened to him, including the exact amount of money that Haman had promised to pay into the royal treasury in order to destroy the Jews.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And Mordecai told him of all that had happened unto him, and of the sum of the money that Haman had promised to pay to the king’s treasuries for the Jews, to destroy them."},"BSB":{"text":"and Mordecai told him all that had happened to him, including the exact amount of money that Haman had promised to pay into the royal treasury in order to destroy the Jews."}},"definableWords":[],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"8":{"text":"Also he gave him the copy of the writing of the decree that was given at Shushan to destroy them, to shew it unto Esther, and to declare it unto her, and to charge her that she should go in unto the king, to make supplication unto him, and to make request before him for her people.","ref":"Esther 4:8","synthesized":"Mordecai also gave Hathach a copy of the written decree issued in Susa for the destruction of the Jews, to show and explain to Esther, urging her to approach the king, implore his favor, and plead before him for her people.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Also he gave him the copy of the writing of the decree that was given at Shushan to destroy them, to shew it unto Esther, and to declare it unto her, and to charge her that she should go in unto the king, to make supplication unto him, and to make request before him for her people."},"BSB":{"text":"Mordecai also gave Hathach a copy of the written decree issued in Susa for the destruction of the Jews, to show and explain to Esther, urging her to approach the king, implore his favor, and plead before him for her people."}},"definableWords":["king","people"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"9":{"text":"And Hatach came and told Esther the words of Mordecai.","ref":"Esther 4:9","synthesized":"So Hathach went back and relayed Mordecai’s response to Esther.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And Hatach came and told Esther the words of Mordecai."},"BSB":{"text":"So Hathach went back and relayed Mordecai’s response to Esther."}},"definableWords":[],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"10":{"text":"Again Esther spake unto Hatach, and gave him commandment unto Mordecai;","ref":"Esther 4:10","synthesized":"Then Esther spoke to Hathach and instructed him to tell Mordecai,","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Again Esther spake unto Hatach, and gave him commandment unto Mordecai;"},"BSB":{"text":"Then Esther spoke to Hathach and instructed him to tell Mordecai,"}},"definableWords":[],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"11":{"text":"All the king’s servants, and the people of the king’s provinces, do know, that whosoever, whether man or woman, shall come unto the king into the inner court, who is not called, there is one law of his to put him to death, except such to whom the king shall hold out the golden sceptre, that he may live: but I have not been called to come in unto the king these thirty days.","ref":"Esther 4:11","synthesized":"“All the royal officials and the people of the king’s provinces know that one law applies to every man or woman who approaches the king in the inner court without being summoned—that he be put to death. Only if the king extends the gold scepter may that person live. But I have not been summoned to appear before the king for the past thirty days.”","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"All the king’s servants, and the people of the king’s provinces, do know, that whosoever, whether man or woman, shall come unto the king into the inner court, who is not called, there is one law of his to put him to death, except such to whom the king shall hold out the golden sceptre, that he may live: but I have not been called to come in unto the king these thirty days."},"BSB":{"text":"“All the royal officials and the people of the king’s provinces know that one law applies to every man or woman who approaches the king in the inner court without being summoned—that he be put to death. Only if the king extends the gold scepter may that person live. But I have not been summoned to appear before the king for the past thirty days.”"}},"definableWords":["people","king","one","law","man","or","woman","King","death","scepter","live","days"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"12":{"text":"And they told to Mordecai Esther’s words.","ref":"Esther 4:12","synthesized":"When Esther’s words were relayed to Mordecai,","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And they told to Mordecai Esther’s words."},"BSB":{"text":"When Esther’s words were relayed to Mordecai,"}},"definableWords":[],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"13":{"text":"Then Mordecai commanded to answer Esther, Think not with thyself that thou shalt escape in the king’s house, more than all the Jews.","ref":"Esther 4:13","synthesized":"he sent back to her this reply: “Do not imagine that because you are in the king’s palace you alone will escape the fate of all the Jews.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Then Mordecai commanded to answer Esther, Think not with thyself that thou shalt escape in the king’s house, more than all the Jews."},"BSB":{"text":"he sent back to her this reply: “Do not imagine that because you are in the king’s palace you alone will escape the fate of all the Jews."}},"definableWords":["king"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"14":{"text":"For if thou altogether holdest thy peace at this time, then shall there enlargement and deliverance arise to the Jews from another place; but thou and thy father’s house shall be destroyed: and who knoweth whether thou art come to the kingdom for such a time as this?","ref":"Esther 4:14","synthesized":"For if you remain silent at this time, relief and deliverance for the Jews will arise from another place, but you and your father’s house will perish. And who knows if perhaps you have come to the kingdom for such a time as this?”","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"For if thou altogether holdest thy peace at this time, then shall there enlargement and deliverance arise to the Jews from another place; but thou and thy father’s house shall be destroyed: and who knoweth whether thou art come to the kingdom for such a time as this?"},"BSB":{"text":"For if you remain silent at this time, relief and deliverance for the Jews will arise from another place, but you and your father’s house will perish. And who knows if perhaps you have come to the kingdom for such a time as this?”"}},"definableWords":["father","house","kingdom"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"15":{"text":"Then Esther bade them return Mordecai this answer,","ref":"Esther 4:15","synthesized":"Then Esther sent this reply to Mordecai:","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Then Esther bade them return Mordecai this answer,"},"BSB":{"text":"Then Esther sent this reply to Mordecai:"}},"definableWords":[],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"16":{"text":"Go, gather together all the Jews that are present in Shushan, and fast ye for me, and neither eat nor drink three days, night or day: I also and my maidens will fast likewise; and so will I go in unto the king, which is not according to the law: and if I perish, I perish.","ref":"Esther 4:16","synthesized":"“Go and assemble all the Jews who can be found in Susa, and fast for me. Do not eat or drink for three days, night or day, and I and my maidens will fast as you do. After that, I will go to the king, even though it is against the law. And if I perish, I perish!”","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Go, gather together all the Jews that are present in Shushan, and fast ye for me, and neither eat nor drink three days, night or day: I also and my maidens will fast likewise; and so will I go in unto the king, which is not according to the law: and if I perish, I perish."},"BSB":{"text":"“Go and assemble all the Jews who can be found in Susa, and fast for me. Do not eat or drink for three days, night or day, and I and my maidens will fast as you do. After that, I will go to the king, even though it is against the law. And if I perish, I perish!”"}},"definableWords":["fast","or","days","night","day","king","law"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"17":{"text":"So Mordecai went his way, and did according to all that Esther had commanded him.","ref":"Esther 4:17","synthesized":"So Mordecai went and did all that Esther had instructed him.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"So Mordecai went his way, and did according to all that Esther had commanded him."},"BSB":{"text":"So Mordecai went and did all that Esther had instructed him."}},"definableWords":[],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]}}},"5":{"chapter":"5","title":"ESTHER'S BANQUET — HAMAN'S GALLOWS","verses":{"1":{"text":"Now it came to pass on the third day, that Esther put on her royal apparel, and stood in the inner court of the king’s house, over against the king’s house: and the king sat upon his royal throne in the royal house, over against the gate of the house.","ref":"Esther 5:1","synthesized":"On the third day, Esther put on her royal attire and stood in the inner court of the palace across from the king’s quarters. The king was sitting on his royal throne in the royal courtroom, facing the entrance.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Now it came to pass on the third day, that Esther put on her royal apparel, and stood in the inner court of the king’s house, over against the king’s house: and the king sat upon his royal throne in the royal house, over against the gate of the house."},"BSB":{"text":"On the third day, Esther put on her royal attire and stood in the inner court of the palace across from the king’s quarters. The king was sitting on his royal throne in the royal courtroom, facing the entrance."}},"definableWords":["day","king","King","throne"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"2":{"text":"And it was so, when the king saw Esther the queen standing in the court, that she obtained favour in his sight: and the king held out to Esther the golden sceptre that was in his hand. So Esther drew near, and touched the top of the sceptre.","ref":"Esther 5:2","synthesized":"As soon as the king saw Queen Esther standing in the court, she found favor in his sight. The king extended the gold scepter in his hand toward Esther, and she approached and touched the tip of the scepter.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And it was so, when the king saw Esther the queen standing in the court, that she obtained favour in his sight: and the king held out to Esther the golden sceptre that was in his hand. So Esther drew near, and touched the top of the sceptre."},"BSB":{"text":"As soon as the king saw Queen Esther standing in the court, she found favor in his sight. The king extended the gold scepter in his hand toward Esther, and she approached and touched the tip of the scepter."}},"definableWords":["king","saw","King","scepter"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"3":{"text":"Then said the king unto her, What wilt thou, queen Esther? and what is thy request? it shall be even given thee to the half of the kingdom.","ref":"Esther 5:3","synthesized":"“What is it, Queen Esther?” the king inquired. “What is your request? Even up to half the kingdom, it will be given to you.”","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Then said the king unto her, What wilt thou, queen Esther? and what is thy request? it shall be even given thee to the half of the kingdom."},"BSB":{"text":"“What is it, Queen Esther?” the king inquired. “What is your request? Even up to half the kingdom, it will be given to you.”"}},"definableWords":["king","kingdom"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"4":{"text":"And Esther answered, If it seem good unto the king, let the king and Haman come this day unto the banquet that I have prepared for him.","ref":"Esther 5:4","synthesized":"“If it pleases the king,” Esther replied, “may the king and Haman come today to the banquet I have prepared for the king.”","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And Esther answered, If it seem good unto the king, let the king and Haman come this day unto the banquet that I have prepared for him."},"BSB":{"text":"“If it pleases the king,” Esther replied, “may the king and Haman come today to the banquet I have prepared for the king.”"}},"definableWords":["king","King"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"5":{"text":"Then the king said, Cause Haman to make haste, that he may do as Esther hath said. So the king and Haman came to the banquet that Esther had prepared.","ref":"Esther 5:5","synthesized":"“Hurry,” commanded the king, “and bring Haman, so we can do as Esther has requested.”  So the king and Haman went to the banquet that Esther had prepared.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Then the king said, Cause Haman to make haste, that he may do as Esther hath said. So the king and Haman came to the banquet that Esther had prepared."},"BSB":{"text":"“Hurry,” commanded the king, “and bring Haman, so we can do as Esther has requested.”  So the king and Haman went to the banquet that Esther had prepared."}},"definableWords":["king","King"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"6":{"text":"And the king said unto Esther at the banquet of wine, What is thy petition? and it shall be granted thee: and what is thy request? even to the half of the kingdom it shall be performed.","ref":"Esther 5:6","synthesized":"And as they drank their wine, the king said to Esther, “What is your petition? It will be given to you. What is your request? Even up to half the kingdom, it will be fulfilled.”","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And the king said unto Esther at the banquet of wine, What is thy petition? and it shall be granted thee: and what is thy request? even to the half of the kingdom it shall be performed."},"BSB":{"text":"And as they drank their wine, the king said to Esther, “What is your petition? It will be given to you. What is your request? Even up to half the kingdom, it will be fulfilled.”"}},"definableWords":["king","kingdom"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"7":{"text":"Then answered Esther, and said, My petition and my request is;","ref":"Esther 5:7","synthesized":"Esther replied, “This is my petition and my request:","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Then answered Esther, and said, My petition and my request is;"},"BSB":{"text":"Esther replied, “This is my petition and my request:"}},"definableWords":[],"peopleInVerse":[]},"8":{"text":"If I have found favour in the sight of the king, and if it please the king to grant my petition, and to perform my request, let the king and Haman come to the banquet that I shall prepare for them, and I will do to morrow as the king hath said.","ref":"Esther 5:8","synthesized":"If I have found favor in the sight of the king, and if it pleases the king to grant my petition and fulfill my request, may the king and Haman come tomorrow to the banquet I will prepare for them. Then I will answer the king’s question.”","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"If I have found favour in the sight of the king, and if it please the king to grant my petition, and to perform my request, let the king and Haman come to the banquet that I shall prepare for them, and I will do to morrow as the king hath said."},"BSB":{"text":"If I have found favor in the sight of the king, and if it pleases the king to grant my petition and fulfill my request, may the king and Haman come tomorrow to the banquet I will prepare for them. Then I will answer the king’s question.”"}},"definableWords":["king","King"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"9":{"text":"Then went Haman forth that day joyful and with a glad heart: but when Haman saw Mordecai in the king’s gate, that he stood not up, nor moved for him, he was full of indignation against Mordecai.","ref":"Esther 5:9","synthesized":"That day Haman went out full of joy and glad of heart. At the king’s gate, however, he saw Mordecai, who did not rise or tremble in fear at his presence. And Haman was filled with rage toward Mordecai.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Then went Haman forth that day joyful and with a glad heart: but when Haman saw Mordecai in the king’s gate, that he stood not up, nor moved for him, he was full of indignation against Mordecai."},"BSB":{"text":"That day Haman went out full of joy and glad of heart. At the king’s gate, however, he saw Mordecai, who did not rise or tremble in fear at his presence. And Haman was filled with rage toward Mordecai."}},"definableWords":["day","joy","heart","king","saw","or","fear"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"10":{"text":"Nevertheless Haman refrained himself: and when he came home, he sent and called for his friends, and Zeresh his wife.","ref":"Esther 5:10","synthesized":"Nevertheless, Haman restrained himself and went home. And calling for his friends and his wife Zeresh,","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Nevertheless Haman refrained himself: and when he came home, he sent and called for his friends, and Zeresh his wife."},"BSB":{"text":"Nevertheless, Haman restrained himself and went home. And calling for his friends and his wife Zeresh,"}},"definableWords":["wife"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"11":{"text":"And Haman told them of the glory of his riches, and the multitude of his children, and all the things wherein the king had promoted him, and how he had advanced him above the princes and servants of the king.","ref":"Esther 5:11","synthesized":"Haman recounted to them his glorious wealth, his many sons, and all the ways the king had honored and promoted him over the other officials and servants.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And Haman told them of the glory of his riches, and the multitude of his children, and all the things wherein the king had promoted him, and how he had advanced him above the princes and servants of the king."},"BSB":{"text":"Haman recounted to them his glorious wealth, his many sons, and all the ways the king had honored and promoted him over the other officials and servants."}},"definableWords":["sons","king","servants"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"12":{"text":"Haman said moreover, Yea, Esther the queen did let no man come in with the king unto the banquet that she had prepared but myself; and to morrow am I invited unto her also with the king.","ref":"Esther 5:12","synthesized":"“What is more,” Haman added, “Queen Esther invited no one but me to join the king at the banquet she prepared, and I am invited back tomorrow along with the king.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Haman said moreover, Yea, Esther the queen did let no man come in with the king unto the banquet that she had prepared but myself; and to morrow am I invited unto her also with the king."},"BSB":{"text":"“What is more,” Haman added, “Queen Esther invited no one but me to join the king at the banquet she prepared, and I am invited back tomorrow along with the king."}},"definableWords":["one","king","King"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"13":{"text":"Yet all this availeth me nothing, so long as I see Mordecai the Jew sitting at the king’s gate.","ref":"Esther 5:13","synthesized":"Yet none of this satisfies me as long as I see Mordecai the Jew sitting at the king’s gate.”","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Yet all this availeth me nothing, so long as I see Mordecai the Jew sitting at the king’s gate."},"BSB":{"text":"Yet none of this satisfies me as long as I see Mordecai the Jew sitting at the king’s gate.”"}},"definableWords":["see","Jew","king"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"14":{"text":"Then said Zeresh his wife and all his friends unto him, Let a gallows be made of fifty cubits high, and to morrow speak thou unto the king that Mordecai may be hanged thereon: then go thou in merrily with the king unto the banquet. And the thing pleased Haman; and he caused the gallows to be made.","ref":"Esther 5:14","synthesized":"His wife Zeresh and all his friends told him, “Have them build a gallows fifty cubits high, and ask the king in the morning to have Mordecai hanged on it. Then go to the banquet with the king and enjoy yourself.”  The advice pleased Haman, and he had the gallows constructed.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Then said Zeresh his wife and all his friends unto him, Let a gallows be made of fifty cubits high, and to morrow speak thou unto the king that Mordecai may be hanged thereon: then go thou in merrily with the king unto the banquet. And the thing pleased Haman; and he caused the gallows to be made."},"BSB":{"text":"His wife Zeresh and all his friends told him, “Have them build a gallows fifty cubits high, and ask the king in the morning to have Mordecai hanged on it. Then go to the banquet with the king and enjoy yourself.”  The advice pleased Haman, and he had the gallows constructed."}},"definableWords":["wife","king","King"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]}}},"6":{"chapter":"6","title":"MORDECAI HONORED","verses":{"1":{"text":"On that night could not the king sleep, and he commanded to bring the book of records of the chronicles; and they were read before the king.","ref":"Esther 6:1","synthesized":"That night sleep escaped the king; so he ordered the Book of Records, the Chronicles, to be brought in and read to him.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"On that night could not the king sleep, and he commanded to bring the book of records of the chronicles; and they were read before the king."},"BSB":{"text":"That night sleep escaped the king; so he ordered the Book of Records, the Chronicles, to be brought in and read to him."}},"definableWords":["night","king"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"2":{"text":"And it was found written, that Mordecai had told of Bigthana and Teresh, two of the king’s chamberlains, the keepers of the door, who sought to lay hand on the king Ahasuerus.","ref":"Esther 6:2","synthesized":"And there it was found recorded that Mordecai had exposed Bigthana and Teresh, two of the eunuchs who guarded the king’s entrance, when they had conspired to assassinate King Xerxes.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And it was found written, that Mordecai had told of Bigthana and Teresh, two of the king’s chamberlains, the keepers of the door, who sought to lay hand on the king Ahasuerus."},"BSB":{"text":"And there it was found recorded that Mordecai had exposed Bigthana and Teresh, two of the eunuchs who guarded the king’s entrance, when they had conspired to assassinate King Xerxes."}},"definableWords":["king","King"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"3":{"text":"And the king said, What honour and dignity hath been done to Mordecai for this? Then said the king’s servants that ministered unto him, There is nothing done for him.","ref":"Esther 6:3","synthesized":"The king inquired, “What honor or dignity has been bestowed on Mordecai for this act?”  “Nothing has been done for him,” replied the king’s attendants.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And the king said, What honour and dignity hath been done to Mordecai for this? Then said the king’s servants that ministered unto him, There is nothing done for him."},"BSB":{"text":"The king inquired, “What honor or dignity has been bestowed on Mordecai for this act?”  “Nothing has been done for him,” replied the king’s attendants."}},"definableWords":["king","or","King"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"4":{"text":"And the king said, Who is in the court? Now Haman was come into the outward court of the king’s house, to speak unto the king to hang Mordecai on the gallows that he had prepared for him.","ref":"Esther 6:4","synthesized":"“Who is in the court?” the king asked.  Now Haman had just entered the outer court of the palace to ask the king to hang Mordecai on the gallows he had prepared for him.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And the king said, Who is in the court? Now Haman was come into the outward court of the king’s house, to speak unto the king to hang Mordecai on the gallows that he had prepared for him."},"BSB":{"text":"“Who is in the court?” the king asked.  Now Haman had just entered the outer court of the palace to ask the king to hang Mordecai on the gallows he had prepared for him."}},"definableWords":["king","King"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"5":{"text":"And the king’s servants said unto him, Behold, Haman standeth in the court. And the king said, Let him come in.","ref":"Esther 6:5","synthesized":"So the king’s attendants answered him, “Haman is there, standing in the court.”  “Bring him in,” ordered the king.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And the king’s servants said unto him, Behold, Haman standeth in the court. And the king said, Let him come in."},"BSB":{"text":"So the king’s attendants answered him, “Haman is there, standing in the court.”  “Bring him in,” ordered the king."}},"definableWords":["king","King"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"6":{"text":"So Haman came in. And the king said unto him, What shall be done unto the man whom the king delighteth to honour? Now Haman thought in his heart, To whom would the king delight to do honour more than to myself?","ref":"Esther 6:6","synthesized":"Haman entered, and the king asked him, “What should be done for the man whom the king is delighted to honor?”  Now Haman thought to himself, “Whom would the king be delighted to honor more than me?”","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"So Haman came in. And the king said unto him, What shall be done unto the man whom the king delighteth to honour? Now Haman thought in his heart, To whom would the king delight to do honour more than to myself?"},"BSB":{"text":"Haman entered, and the king asked him, “What should be done for the man whom the king is delighted to honor?”  Now Haman thought to himself, “Whom would the king be delighted to honor more than me?”"}},"definableWords":["king","man","King"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"7":{"text":"And Haman answered the king, For the man whom the king delighteth to honour,","ref":"Esther 6:7","synthesized":"And Haman told the king, “For the man whom the king is delighted to honor,","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And Haman answered the king, For the man whom the king delighteth to honour,"},"BSB":{"text":"And Haman told the king, “For the man whom the king is delighted to honor,"}},"definableWords":["king","man","King"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"8":{"text":"Let the royal apparel be brought which the king useth to wear, and the horse that the king rideth upon, and the crown royal which is set upon his head:","ref":"Esther 6:8","synthesized":"have them bring a royal robe that the king himself has worn and a horse on which the king himself has ridden—one with a royal crest placed on its head.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Let the royal apparel be brought which the king useth to wear, and the horse that the king rideth upon, and the crown royal which is set upon his head:"},"BSB":{"text":"have them bring a royal robe that the king himself has worn and a horse on which the king himself has ridden—one with a royal crest placed on its head."}},"definableWords":["king","King","one"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"9":{"text":"And let this apparel and horse be delivered to the hand of one of the king’s most noble princes, that they may array the man withal whom the king delighteth to honour, and bring him on horseback through the street of the city, and proclaim before him, Thus shall it be done to the man whom the king delighteth to honour.","ref":"Esther 6:9","synthesized":"Let the robe and the horse be entrusted to one of the king’s most noble princes. Let them array the man the king wants to honor and parade him on the horse through the city square, proclaiming before him, ‘This is what is done for the man whom the king is delighted to honor!’”","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And let this apparel and horse be delivered to the hand of one of the king’s most noble princes, that they may array the man withal whom the king delighteth to honour, and bring him on horseback through the street of the city, and proclaim before him, Thus shall it be done to the man whom the king delighteth to honour."},"BSB":{"text":"Let the robe and the horse be entrusted to one of the king’s most noble princes. Let them array the man the king wants to honor and parade him on the horse through the city square, proclaiming before him, ‘This is what is done for the man whom the king is delighted to honor!’”"}},"definableWords":["one","king","man","King"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"10":{"text":"Then the king said to Haman, Make haste, and take the apparel and the horse, as thou hast said, and do even so to Mordecai the Jew, that sitteth at the king’s gate: let nothing fail of all that thou hast spoken.","ref":"Esther 6:10","synthesized":"“Hurry,” said the king to Haman, “and do just as you proposed. Take the robe and the horse to Mordecai the Jew, who is sitting at the king’s gate. Do not neglect anything that you have suggested.”","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Then the king said to Haman, Make haste, and take the apparel and the horse, as thou hast said, and do even so to Mordecai the Jew, that sitteth at the king’s gate: let nothing fail of all that thou hast spoken."},"BSB":{"text":"“Hurry,” said the king to Haman, “and do just as you proposed. Take the robe and the horse to Mordecai the Jew, who is sitting at the king’s gate. Do not neglect anything that you have suggested.”"}},"definableWords":["king","Jew","King"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"11":{"text":"Then took Haman the apparel and the horse, and arrayed Mordecai, and brought him on horseback through the street of the city, and proclaimed before him, Thus shall it be done unto the man whom the king delighteth to honour.","ref":"Esther 6:11","synthesized":"So Haman took the robe and the horse, arrayed Mordecai, and paraded him through the city square, crying out before him, “This is what is done for the man whom the king is delighted to honor!”","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Then took Haman the apparel and the horse, and arrayed Mordecai, and brought him on horseback through the street of the city, and proclaimed before him, Thus shall it be done unto the man whom the king delighteth to honour."},"BSB":{"text":"So Haman took the robe and the horse, arrayed Mordecai, and paraded him through the city square, crying out before him, “This is what is done for the man whom the king is delighted to honor!”"}},"definableWords":["man","king"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"12":{"text":"And Mordecai came again to the king’s gate. But Haman hasted to his house mourning, and having his head covered.","ref":"Esther 6:12","synthesized":"Then Mordecai returned to the king’s gate. But Haman rushed home, with his head covered in grief.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And Mordecai came again to the king’s gate. But Haman hasted to his house mourning, and having his head covered."},"BSB":{"text":"Then Mordecai returned to the king’s gate. But Haman rushed home, with his head covered in grief."}},"definableWords":["king"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"13":{"text":"And Haman told Zeresh his wife and all his friends every thing that had befallen him. Then said his wise men and Zeresh his wife unto him, If Mordecai be of the seed of the Jews, before whom thou hast begun to fall, thou shalt not prevail against him, but shalt surely fall before him.","ref":"Esther 6:13","synthesized":"Haman told his wife Zeresh and all his friends everything that had happened. His advisers and his wife Zeresh said to him, “Since Mordecai, before whom your downfall has begun, is Jewish, you will not prevail against him—for surely you will fall before him.”","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And Haman told Zeresh his wife and all his friends every thing that had befallen him. Then said his wise men and Zeresh his wife unto him, If Mordecai be of the seed of the Jews, before whom thou hast begun to fall, thou shalt not prevail against him, but shalt surely fall before him."},"BSB":{"text":"Haman told his wife Zeresh and all his friends everything that had happened. His advisers and his wife Zeresh said to him, “Since Mordecai, before whom your downfall has begun, is Jewish, you will not prevail against him—for surely you will fall before him.”"}},"definableWords":["wife"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"14":{"text":"And while they were yet talking with him, came the king’s chamberlains, and hasted to bring Haman unto the banquet that Esther had prepared.","ref":"Esther 6:14","synthesized":"While they were still speaking with Haman, the king’s eunuchs arrived and rushed him to the banquet that Esther had prepared.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And while they were yet talking with him, came the king’s chamberlains, and hasted to bring Haman unto the banquet that Esther had prepared."},"BSB":{"text":"While they were still speaking with Haman, the king’s eunuchs arrived and rushed him to the banquet that Esther had prepared."}},"definableWords":["king"],"peopleInVerse":[]}}},"7":{"chapter":"7","title":"HAMAN HANGED","verses":{"1":{"text":"So the king and Haman came to banquet with Esther the queen.","ref":"Esther 7:1","synthesized":"So the king and Haman went to dine with Esther the queen,","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"So the king and Haman came to banquet with Esther the queen."},"BSB":{"text":"So the king and Haman went to dine with Esther the queen,"}},"definableWords":["king"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"2":{"text":"And the king said again unto Esther on the second day at the banquet of wine, What is thy petition, queen Esther? and it shall be granted thee: and what is thy request? and it shall be performed, even to the half of the kingdom.","ref":"Esther 7:2","synthesized":"and as they drank their wine on that second day, the king asked once more, “Queen Esther, what is your petition? It will be given to you. What is your request? Even up to half the kingdom, it will be fulfilled.”","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And the king said again unto Esther on the second day at the banquet of wine, What is thy petition, queen Esther? and it shall be granted thee: and what is thy request? and it shall be performed, even to the half of the kingdom."},"BSB":{"text":"and as they drank their wine on that second day, the king asked once more, “Queen Esther, what is your petition? It will be given to you. What is your request? Even up to half the kingdom, it will be fulfilled.”"}},"definableWords":["day","king","kingdom"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"3":{"text":"Then Esther the queen answered and said, If I have found favour in thy sight, O king, and if it please the king, let my life be given me at my petition, and my people at my request:","ref":"Esther 7:3","synthesized":"Queen Esther replied, “If I have found favor in your sight, O king, and if it pleases the king, grant me my life as my petition, and the lives of my people as my request.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Then Esther the queen answered and said, If I have found favour in thy sight, O king, and if it please the king, let my life be given me at my petition, and my people at my request:"},"BSB":{"text":"Queen Esther replied, “If I have found favor in your sight, O king, and if it pleases the king, grant me my life as my petition, and the lives of my people as my request."}},"definableWords":["king","King","life","people"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"4":{"text":"For we are sold, I and my people, to be destroyed, to be slain, and to perish. But if we had been sold for bondmen and bondwomen, I had held my tongue, although the enemy could not countervail the king’s damage.","ref":"Esther 7:4","synthesized":"For my people and I have been sold out to destruction, death, and annihilation. If we had merely been sold as menservants and maidservants, I would have remained silent, because no such distress would justify burdening the king.”","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"For we are sold, I and my people, to be destroyed, to be slain, and to perish. But if we had been sold for bondmen and bondwomen, I had held my tongue, although the enemy could not countervail the king’s damage."},"BSB":{"text":"For my people and I have been sold out to destruction, death, and annihilation. If we had merely been sold as menservants and maidservants, I would have remained silent, because no such distress would justify burdening the king.”"}},"definableWords":["people","death","king"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"5":{"text":"Then the king Ahasuerus answered and said unto Esther the queen, Who is he, and where is he, that durst presume in his heart to do so?","ref":"Esther 7:5","synthesized":"Then King Xerxes spoke up and asked Queen Esther, “Who is this, and where is the one who would devise such a scheme?”","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Then the king Ahasuerus answered and said unto Esther the queen, Who is he, and where is he, that durst presume in his heart to do so?"},"BSB":{"text":"Then King Xerxes spoke up and asked Queen Esther, “Who is this, and where is the one who would devise such a scheme?”"}},"definableWords":["King","one"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"6":{"text":"And Esther said, The adversary and enemy is this wicked Haman. Then Haman was afraid before the king and the queen.","ref":"Esther 7:6","synthesized":"Esther replied, “The adversary and enemy is this wicked man—Haman!”  And Haman stood in terror before the king and queen.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And Esther said, The adversary and enemy is this wicked Haman. Then Haman was afraid before the king and the queen."},"BSB":{"text":"Esther replied, “The adversary and enemy is this wicked man—Haman!”  And Haman stood in terror before the king and queen."}},"definableWords":["man","king"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"7":{"text":"And the king arising from the banquet of wine in his wrath went into the palace garden: and Haman stood up to make request for his life to Esther the queen; for he saw that there was evil determined against him by the king.","ref":"Esther 7:7","synthesized":"In his fury, the king arose from drinking his wine and went to the palace garden, while Haman stayed behind to beg Queen Esther for his life, for he realized that the king was planning a terrible fate for him.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And the king arising from the banquet of wine in his wrath went into the palace garden: and Haman stood up to make request for his life to Esther the queen; for he saw that there was evil determined against him by the king."},"BSB":{"text":"In his fury, the king arose from drinking his wine and went to the palace garden, while Haman stayed behind to beg Queen Esther for his life, for he realized that the king was planning a terrible fate for him."}},"definableWords":["king","garden","life","King"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"8":{"text":"Then the king returned out of the palace garden into the place of the banquet of wine; and Haman was fallen upon the bed whereon Esther was. Then said the king, Will he force the queen also before me in the house? As the word went out of the king’s mouth, they covered Haman’s face.","ref":"Esther 7:8","synthesized":"Just as the king returned from the palace garden to the banquet hall, Haman was falling on the couch where Esther was reclining. The king exclaimed, “Would he actually assault the queen while I am in the palace?”  As soon as the words had left the king’s mouth, they covered Haman’s face.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Then the king returned out of the palace garden into the place of the banquet of wine; and Haman was fallen upon the bed whereon Esther was. Then said the king, Will he force the queen also before me in the house? As the word went out of the king’s mouth, they covered Haman’s face."},"BSB":{"text":"Just as the king returned from the palace garden to the banquet hall, Haman was falling on the couch where Esther was reclining. The king exclaimed, “Would he actually assault the queen while I am in the palace?”  As soon as the words had left the king’s mouth, they covered Haman’s face."}},"definableWords":["king","garden","King"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"9":{"text":"And Harbonah, one of the chamberlains, said before the king, Behold also, the gallows fifty cubits high, which Haman had made for Mordecai, who had spoken good for the king, standeth in the house of Haman. Then the king said, Hang him thereon.","ref":"Esther 7:9","synthesized":"Then Harbonah, one of the eunuchs attending the king, said: “There is a gallows fifty cubits high at Haman’s house. He had it built for Mordecai, who gave the report that saved the king.”  “Hang him on it!” declared the king.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And Harbonah, one of the chamberlains, said before the king, Behold also, the gallows fifty cubits high, which Haman had made for Mordecai, who had spoken good for the king, standeth in the house of Haman. Then the king said, Hang him thereon."},"BSB":{"text":"Then Harbonah, one of the eunuchs attending the king, said: “There is a gallows fifty cubits high at Haman’s house. He had it built for Mordecai, who gave the report that saved the king.”  “Hang him on it!” declared the king."}},"definableWords":["one","king","house","King"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"10":{"text":"So they hanged Haman on the gallows that he had prepared for Mordecai. Then was the king’s wrath pacified.","ref":"Esther 7:10","synthesized":"So they hanged Haman on the gallows he had prepared for Mordecai. Then the fury of the king subsided.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"So they hanged Haman on the gallows that he had prepared for Mordecai. Then was the king’s wrath pacified."},"BSB":{"text":"So they hanged Haman on the gallows he had prepared for Mordecai. Then the fury of the king subsided."}},"definableWords":["king"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]}}},"8":{"chapter":"8","title":"THE JEWS ALLOWED TO DEFEND THEMSELVES","verses":{"1":{"text":"On that day did the king Ahasuerus give the house of Haman the Jews’ enemy unto Esther the queen. And Mordecai came before the king; for Esther had told what he was unto her.","ref":"Esther 8:1","synthesized":"That same day King Xerxes awarded Queen Esther the estate of Haman, the enemy of the Jews. And Mordecai entered the king’s presence because Esther had revealed his relation to her.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"On that day did the king Ahasuerus give the house of Haman the Jews’ enemy unto Esther the queen. And Mordecai came before the king; for Esther had told what he was unto her."},"BSB":{"text":"That same day King Xerxes awarded Queen Esther the estate of Haman, the enemy of the Jews. And Mordecai entered the king’s presence because Esther had revealed his relation to her."}},"definableWords":["day","King","king"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"2":{"text":"And the king took off his ring, which he had taken from Haman, and gave it unto Mordecai. And Esther set Mordecai over the house of Haman.","ref":"Esther 8:2","synthesized":"The king removed the signet ring he had recovered from Haman and presented it to Mordecai. And Esther appointed Mordecai over the estate of Haman.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And the king took off his ring, which he had taken from Haman, and gave it unto Mordecai. And Esther set Mordecai over the house of Haman."},"BSB":{"text":"The king removed the signet ring he had recovered from Haman and presented it to Mordecai. And Esther appointed Mordecai over the estate of Haman."}},"definableWords":["king"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"3":{"text":"And Esther spake yet again before the king, and fell down at his feet, and besought him with tears to put away the mischief of Haman the Agagite, and his device that he had devised against the Jews.","ref":"Esther 8:3","synthesized":"And once again, Esther addressed the king. She fell at his feet weeping and begged him to revoke the evil scheme of Haman the Agagite, which he had devised against the Jews.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And Esther spake yet again before the king, and fell down at his feet, and besought him with tears to put away the mischief of Haman the Agagite, and his device that he had devised against the Jews."},"BSB":{"text":"And once again, Esther addressed the king. She fell at his feet weeping and begged him to revoke the evil scheme of Haman the Agagite, which he had devised against the Jews."}},"definableWords":["king","evil"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"4":{"text":"Then the king held out the golden sceptre toward Esther. So Esther arose, and stood before the king,","ref":"Esther 8:4","synthesized":"The king extended the gold scepter toward Esther, and she arose and stood before the king.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Then the king held out the golden sceptre toward Esther. So Esther arose, and stood before the king,"},"BSB":{"text":"The king extended the gold scepter toward Esther, and she arose and stood before the king."}},"definableWords":["king","scepter","King"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"5":{"text":"And said, If it please the king, and if I have found favour in his sight, and the thing seem right before the king, and I be pleasing in his eyes, let it be written to reverse the letters devised by Haman the son of Hammedatha the Agagite, which he wrote to destroy the Jews which are in all the king’s provinces:","ref":"Esther 8:5","synthesized":"“If it pleases the king,” she said, “and if I have found favor in his sight, and the matter seems proper to the king, and I am pleasing in his sight, may an order be written to revoke the letters that the scheming Haman son of Hammedatha, the Agagite, wrote to destroy the Jews in all the king’s provinces.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And said, If it please the king, and if I have found favour in his sight, and the thing seem right before the king, and I be pleasing in his eyes, let it be written to reverse the letters devised by Haman the son of Hammedatha the Agagite, which he wrote to destroy the Jews which are in all the king’s provinces:"},"BSB":{"text":"“If it pleases the king,” she said, “and if I have found favor in his sight, and the matter seems proper to the king, and I am pleasing in his sight, may an order be written to revoke the letters that the scheming Haman son of Hammedatha, the Agagite, wrote to destroy the Jews in all the king’s provinces."}},"definableWords":["king","King","son"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"6":{"text":"For how can I endure to see the evil that shall come unto my people? or how can I endure to see the destruction of my kindred?","ref":"Esther 8:6","synthesized":"For how could I bear to see the disaster that would befall my people? How could I bear to see the destruction of my kindred?”","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"For how can I endure to see the evil that shall come unto my people? or how can I endure to see the destruction of my kindred?"},"BSB":{"text":"For how could I bear to see the disaster that would befall my people? How could I bear to see the destruction of my kindred?”"}},"definableWords":["see","people"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"7":{"text":"Then the king Ahasuerus said unto Esther the queen and to Mordecai the Jew, Behold, I have given Esther the house of Haman, and him they have hanged upon the gallows, because he laid his hand upon the Jews.","ref":"Esther 8:7","synthesized":"So King Xerxes said to Esther the Queen and Mordecai the Jew, “Behold, I have given Haman’s estate to Esther, and he was hanged on the gallows because he attacked the Jews.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Then the king Ahasuerus said unto Esther the queen and to Mordecai the Jew, Behold, I have given Esther the house of Haman, and him they have hanged upon the gallows, because he laid his hand upon the Jews."},"BSB":{"text":"So King Xerxes said to Esther the Queen and Mordecai the Jew, “Behold, I have given Haman’s estate to Esther, and he was hanged on the gallows because he attacked the Jews."}},"definableWords":["King","Jew"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"8":{"text":"Write ye also for the Jews, as it liketh you, in the king’s name, and seal it with the king’s ring: for the writing which is written in the king’s name, and sealed with the king’s ring, may no man reverse.","ref":"Esther 8:8","synthesized":"Now you may write in the king’s name as you please regarding the Jews, and seal it with the royal signet ring. For a decree that is written in the name of the king and sealed with the royal signet ring cannot be revoked.”","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Write ye also for the Jews, as it liketh you, in the king’s name, and seal it with the king’s ring: for the writing which is written in the king’s name, and sealed with the king’s ring, may no man reverse."},"BSB":{"text":"Now you may write in the king’s name as you please regarding the Jews, and seal it with the royal signet ring. For a decree that is written in the name of the king and sealed with the royal signet ring cannot be revoked.”"}},"definableWords":["king","name","King"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"9":{"text":"Then were the king’s scribes called at that time in the third month, that is, the month Sivan, on the three and twentieth day thereof; and it was written according to all that Mordecai commanded unto the Jews, and to the lieutenants, and the deputies and rulers of the provinces which are from India unto Ethiopia, an hundred twenty and seven provinces, unto every province according to the writing thereof, and unto every people after their language, and to the Jews according to their writing, and according to their language.","ref":"Esther 8:9","synthesized":"At once the royal scribes were summoned, and on the twenty-third day of the third month (the month of Sivan), they recorded all of Mordecai’s orders to the Jews and to the satraps, governors, and princes of the 127 provinces from India to Cush—writing to each province in its own script, to every people in their own language, and to the Jews in their own script and language.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Then were the king’s scribes called at that time in the third month, that is, the month Sivan, on the three and twentieth day thereof; and it was written according to all that Mordecai commanded unto the Jews, and to the lieutenants, and the deputies and rulers of the provinces which are from India unto Ethiopia, an hundred twenty and seven provinces, unto every province according to the writing thereof, and unto every people after their language, and to the Jews according to their writing, and according to their language."},"BSB":{"text":"At once the royal scribes were summoned, and on the twenty-third day of the third month (the month of Sivan), they recorded all of Mordecai’s orders to the Jews and to the satraps, governors, and princes of the 127 provinces from India to Cush—writing to each province in its own script, to every people in their own language, and to the Jews in their own script and language."}},"definableWords":["day","people"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai","Cush"]},"10":{"text":"And he wrote in the king Ahasuerus’ name, and sealed it with the king’s ring, and sent letters by posts on horseback, and riders on mules, camels, and young dromedaries:","ref":"Esther 8:10","synthesized":"Mordecai wrote in the name of King Xerxes and sealed it with the royal signet ring. He sent the documents by mounted couriers riding on swift horses bred from the royal mares.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And he wrote in the king Ahasuerus’ name, and sealed it with the king’s ring, and sent letters by posts on horseback, and riders on mules, camels, and young dromedaries:"},"BSB":{"text":"Mordecai wrote in the name of King Xerxes and sealed it with the royal signet ring. He sent the documents by mounted couriers riding on swift horses bred from the royal mares."}},"definableWords":["name","King"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"11":{"text":"Wherein the king granted the Jews which were in every city to gather themselves together, and to stand for their life, to destroy, to slay, and to cause to perish, all the power of the people and province that would assault them, both little ones and women, and to take the spoil of them for a prey,","ref":"Esther 8:11","synthesized":"By these letters the king permitted the Jews in each and every city the right to assemble and defend themselves, to destroy, kill, and annihilate all the forces of any people or province hostile to them, including women and children, and to plunder their possessions.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Wherein the king granted the Jews which were in every city to gather themselves together, and to stand for their life, to destroy, to slay, and to cause to perish, all the power of the people and province that would assault them, both little ones and women, and to take the spoil of them for a prey,"},"BSB":{"text":"By these letters the king permitted the Jews in each and every city the right to assemble and defend themselves, to destroy, kill, and annihilate all the forces of any people or province hostile to them, including women and children, and to plunder their possessions."}},"definableWords":["king","people","or","women"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"12":{"text":"Upon one day in all the provinces of king Ahasuerus, namely, upon the thirteenth day of the twelfth month, which is the month Adar.","ref":"Esther 8:12","synthesized":"The single day appointed throughout all the provinces of King Xerxes was the thirteenth day of the twelfth month, the month of Adar.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Upon one day in all the provinces of king Ahasuerus, namely, upon the thirteenth day of the twelfth month, which is the month Adar."},"BSB":{"text":"The single day appointed throughout all the provinces of King Xerxes was the thirteenth day of the twelfth month, the month of Adar."}},"definableWords":["day","King"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"13":{"text":"The copy of the writing for a commandment to be given in every province was published unto all people, and that the Jews should be ready against that day to avenge themselves on their enemies.","ref":"Esther 8:13","synthesized":"A copy of the text of the edict was to be issued in every province and published to all the people, so that the Jews would be ready on that day to avenge themselves on their enemies.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"The copy of the writing for a commandment to be given in every province was published unto all people, and that the Jews should be ready against that day to avenge themselves on their enemies."},"BSB":{"text":"A copy of the text of the edict was to be issued in every province and published to all the people, so that the Jews would be ready on that day to avenge themselves on their enemies."}},"definableWords":["people","day"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"14":{"text":"So the posts that rode upon mules and camels went out, being hastened and pressed on by the king’s commandment. And the decree was given at Shushan the palace.","ref":"Esther 8:14","synthesized":"The couriers rode out in haste on their royal horses, pressed on by the command of the king. And the edict was also issued in the citadel of Susa.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"So the posts that rode upon mules and camels went out, being hastened and pressed on by the king’s commandment. And the decree was given at Shushan the palace."},"BSB":{"text":"The couriers rode out in haste on their royal horses, pressed on by the command of the king. And the edict was also issued in the citadel of Susa."}},"definableWords":["king"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"15":{"text":"And Mordecai went out from the presence of the king in royal apparel of blue and white, and with a great crown of gold, and with a garment of fine linen and purple: and the city of Shushan rejoiced and was glad.","ref":"Esther 8:15","synthesized":"Mordecai went out from the presence of the king in royal garments of blue and white, with a large gold crown and a purple robe of fine linen. And the city of Susa shouted and rejoiced.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And Mordecai went out from the presence of the king in royal apparel of blue and white, and with a great crown of gold, and with a garment of fine linen and purple: and the city of Shushan rejoiced and was glad."},"BSB":{"text":"Mordecai went out from the presence of the king in royal garments of blue and white, with a large gold crown and a purple robe of fine linen. And the city of Susa shouted and rejoiced."}},"definableWords":["king","crown"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"16":{"text":"The Jews had light, and gladness, and joy, and honour.","ref":"Esther 8:16","synthesized":"For the Jews it was a time of light and gladness, of joy and honor.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"The Jews had light, and gladness, and joy, and honour."},"BSB":{"text":"For the Jews it was a time of light and gladness, of joy and honor."}},"definableWords":["light","joy"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"17":{"text":"And in every province, and in every city, whithersoever the king’s commandment and his decree came, the Jews had joy and gladness, a feast and a good day. And many of the people of the land became Jews; for the fear of the Jews fell upon them.","ref":"Esther 8:17","synthesized":"In every province and every city, wherever the king’s edict and decree reached, there was joy and gladness among the Jews, with feasting and celebrating. And many of the people of the land themselves became Jews, because the fear of the Jews had fallen upon them.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And in every province, and in every city, whithersoever the king’s commandment and his decree came, the Jews had joy and gladness, a feast and a good day. And many of the people of the land became Jews; for the fear of the Jews fell upon them."},"BSB":{"text":"In every province and every city, wherever the king’s edict and decree reached, there was joy and gladness among the Jews, with feasting and celebrating. And many of the people of the land themselves became Jews, because the fear of the Jews had fallen upon them."}},"definableWords":["king","joy","people","land","fear"],"peopleInVerse":[]}}},"9":{"chapter":"9","title":"PURIM ESTABLISHED","verses":{"1":{"text":"Now in the twelfth month, that is, the month Adar, on the thirteenth day of the same, when the king’s commandment and his decree drew near to be put in execution, in the day that the enemies of the Jews hoped to have power over them, (though it was turned to the contrary, that the Jews had rule over them that hated them;)","ref":"Esther 9:1","synthesized":"On the thirteenth day of the twelfth month, the month of Adar, the king’s command and edict were to be executed. On this day the enemies of the Jews had hoped to overpower them, but their plan was overturned and the Jews overpowered those who hated them.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Now in the twelfth month, that is, the month Adar, on the thirteenth day of the same, when the king’s commandment and his decree drew near to be put in execution, in the day that the enemies of the Jews hoped to have power over them, (though it was turned to the contrary, that the Jews had rule over them that hated them;)"},"BSB":{"text":"On the thirteenth day of the twelfth month, the month of Adar, the king’s command and edict were to be executed. On this day the enemies of the Jews had hoped to overpower them, but their plan was overturned and the Jews overpowered those who hated them."}},"definableWords":["day","king"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"2":{"text":"The Jews gathered themselves together in their cities throughout all the provinces of the king Ahasuerus, to lay hand on such as sought their hurt: and no man could withstand them; for the fear of them fell upon all people.","ref":"Esther 9:2","synthesized":"In each of the provinces of King Xerxes, the Jews assembled in their cities to attack those who sought to harm them. No man could withstand them, because the fear of them had fallen upon all peoples.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"The Jews gathered themselves together in their cities throughout all the provinces of the king Ahasuerus, to lay hand on such as sought their hurt: and no man could withstand them; for the fear of them fell upon all people."},"BSB":{"text":"In each of the provinces of King Xerxes, the Jews assembled in their cities to attack those who sought to harm them. No man could withstand them, because the fear of them had fallen upon all peoples."}},"definableWords":["King","man","fear"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"3":{"text":"And all the rulers of the provinces, and the lieutenants, and the deputies, and officers of the king, helped the Jews; because the fear of Mordecai fell upon them.","ref":"Esther 9:3","synthesized":"And all the officials of the provinces, the satraps, the governors, and the king’s administrators helped the Jews, because the fear of Mordecai had fallen upon them.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And all the rulers of the provinces, and the lieutenants, and the deputies, and officers of the king, helped the Jews; because the fear of Mordecai fell upon them."},"BSB":{"text":"And all the officials of the provinces, the satraps, the governors, and the king’s administrators helped the Jews, because the fear of Mordecai had fallen upon them."}},"definableWords":["king","fear"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"4":{"text":"For Mordecai was great in the king’s house, and his fame went out throughout all the provinces: for this man Mordecai waxed greater and greater.","ref":"Esther 9:4","synthesized":"For Mordecai exercised great power in the palace, and his fame spread throughout the provinces as he became more and more powerful.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"For Mordecai was great in the king’s house, and his fame went out throughout all the provinces: for this man Mordecai waxed greater and greater."},"BSB":{"text":"For Mordecai exercised great power in the palace, and his fame spread throughout the provinces as he became more and more powerful."}},"definableWords":["great"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"5":{"text":"Thus the Jews smote all their enemies with the stroke of the sword, and slaughter, and destruction, and did what they would unto those that hated them.","ref":"Esther 9:5","synthesized":"The Jews put all their enemies to the sword, killing and destroying them, and they did as they pleased to those who hated them.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Thus the Jews smote all their enemies with the stroke of the sword, and slaughter, and destruction, and did what they would unto those that hated them."},"BSB":{"text":"The Jews put all their enemies to the sword, killing and destroying them, and they did as they pleased to those who hated them."}},"definableWords":[],"peopleInVerse":[]},"6":{"text":"And in Shushan the palace the Jews slew and destroyed five hundred men.","ref":"Esther 9:6","synthesized":"In the citadel of Susa, the Jews killed and destroyed five hundred men,","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And in Shushan the palace the Jews slew and destroyed five hundred men."},"BSB":{"text":"In the citadel of Susa, the Jews killed and destroyed five hundred men,"}},"definableWords":["men"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"7":{"text":"And Parshandatha, and Dalphon, and Aspatha,","ref":"Esther 9:7","synthesized":"including Parshandatha, Dalphon, Aspatha,","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And Parshandatha, and Dalphon, and Aspatha,"},"BSB":{"text":"including Parshandatha, Dalphon, Aspatha,"}},"definableWords":[],"peopleInVerse":[]},"8":{"text":"And Poratha, and Adalia, and Aridatha,","ref":"Esther 9:8","synthesized":"Poratha, Adalia, Aridatha,","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And Poratha, and Adalia, and Aridatha,"},"BSB":{"text":"Poratha, Adalia, Aridatha,"}},"definableWords":[],"peopleInVerse":[]},"9":{"text":"And Parmashta, and Arisai, and Aridai, and Vajezatha,","ref":"Esther 9:9","synthesized":"Parmashta, Arisai, Aridai, and Vaizatha.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And Parmashta, and Arisai, and Aridai, and Vajezatha,"},"BSB":{"text":"Parmashta, Arisai, Aridai, and Vaizatha."}},"definableWords":[],"peopleInVerse":[]},"10":{"text":"The ten sons of Haman the son of Hammedatha, the enemy of the Jews, slew they; but on the spoil laid they not their hand.","ref":"Esther 9:10","synthesized":"They killed these ten sons of Haman son of Hammedatha, the enemy of the Jews, but they did not lay a hand on the plunder.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"The ten sons of Haman the son of Hammedatha, the enemy of the Jews, slew they; but on the spoil laid they not their hand."},"BSB":{"text":"They killed these ten sons of Haman son of Hammedatha, the enemy of the Jews, but they did not lay a hand on the plunder."}},"definableWords":["sons","son"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"11":{"text":"On that day the number of those that were slain in Shushan the palace was brought before the king.","ref":"Esther 9:11","synthesized":"On that day the number of those killed in the citadel of Susa was reported to the king,","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"On that day the number of those that were slain in Shushan the palace was brought before the king."},"BSB":{"text":"On that day the number of those killed in the citadel of Susa was reported to the king,"}},"definableWords":["day","king"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"12":{"text":"And the king said unto Esther the queen, The Jews have slain and destroyed five hundred men in Shushan the palace, and the ten sons of Haman; what have they done in the rest of the king’s provinces? now what is thy petition? and it shall be granted thee: or what is thy request further? and it shall be done.","ref":"Esther 9:12","synthesized":"who said to Queen Esther, “In the citadel of Susa the Jews have killed and destroyed five hundred men, including Haman’s ten sons. What have they done in the rest of the royal provinces? Now what is your petition? It will be given to you. And what further do you request? It will be fulfilled.”","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And the king said unto Esther the queen, The Jews have slain and destroyed five hundred men in Shushan the palace, and the ten sons of Haman; what have they done in the rest of the king’s provinces? now what is thy petition? and it shall be granted thee: or what is thy request further? and it shall be done."},"BSB":{"text":"who said to Queen Esther, “In the citadel of Susa the Jews have killed and destroyed five hundred men, including Haman’s ten sons. What have they done in the rest of the royal provinces? Now what is your petition? It will be given to you. And what further do you request? It will be fulfilled.”"}},"definableWords":["men","sons","rest"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"13":{"text":"Then said Esther, If it please the king, let it be granted to the Jews which are in Shushan to do to morrow also according unto this day’s decree, and let Haman’s ten sons be hanged upon the gallows.","ref":"Esther 9:13","synthesized":"Esther replied, “If it pleases the king, may the Jews in Susa also have tomorrow to carry out today’s edict, and may the bodies of Haman’s ten sons be hanged on the gallows.”","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Then said Esther, If it please the king, let it be granted to the Jews which are in Shushan to do to morrow also according unto this day’s decree, and let Haman’s ten sons be hanged upon the gallows."},"BSB":{"text":"Esther replied, “If it pleases the king, may the Jews in Susa also have tomorrow to carry out today’s edict, and may the bodies of Haman’s ten sons be hanged on the gallows.”"}},"definableWords":["king","sons"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"14":{"text":"And the king commanded it so to be done: and the decree was given at Shushan; and they hanged Haman’s ten sons.","ref":"Esther 9:14","synthesized":"So the king commanded that this be done. An edict was issued in Susa, and they hanged the ten sons of Haman.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And the king commanded it so to be done: and the decree was given at Shushan; and they hanged Haman’s ten sons."},"BSB":{"text":"So the king commanded that this be done. An edict was issued in Susa, and they hanged the ten sons of Haman."}},"definableWords":["king","sons"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"15":{"text":"For the Jews that were in Shushan gathered themselves together on the fourteenth day also of the month Adar, and slew three hundred men at Shushan; but on the prey they laid not their hand.","ref":"Esther 9:15","synthesized":"On the fourteenth day of the month of Adar, the Jews in Susa came together again and put to death three hundred men there, but they did not lay a hand on the plunder.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"For the Jews that were in Shushan gathered themselves together on the fourteenth day also of the month Adar, and slew three hundred men at Shushan; but on the prey they laid not their hand."},"BSB":{"text":"On the fourteenth day of the month of Adar, the Jews in Susa came together again and put to death three hundred men there, but they did not lay a hand on the plunder."}},"definableWords":["day","death","men"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"16":{"text":"But the other Jews that were in the king’s provinces gathered themselves together, and stood for their lives, and had rest from their enemies, and slew of their foes seventy and five thousand, but they laid not their hands on the prey,","ref":"Esther 9:16","synthesized":"The rest of the Jews in the royal provinces also assembled to defend themselves and rid themselves of their enemies. They killed 75,000 who hated them, but they did not lay a hand on the plunder.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"But the other Jews that were in the king’s provinces gathered themselves together, and stood for their lives, and had rest from their enemies, and slew of their foes seventy and five thousand, but they laid not their hands on the prey,"},"BSB":{"text":"The rest of the Jews in the royal provinces also assembled to defend themselves and rid themselves of their enemies. They killed 75,000 who hated them, but they did not lay a hand on the plunder."}},"definableWords":["rest"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"17":{"text":"On the thirteenth day of the month Adar; and on the fourteenth day of the same rested they, and made it a day of feasting and gladness.","ref":"Esther 9:17","synthesized":"This was done on the thirteenth day of the month of Adar, and on the fourteenth day they rested, making it a day of feasting and joy.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"On the thirteenth day of the month Adar; and on the fourteenth day of the same rested they, and made it a day of feasting and gladness."},"BSB":{"text":"This was done on the thirteenth day of the month of Adar, and on the fourteenth day they rested, making it a day of feasting and joy."}},"definableWords":["day","joy"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"18":{"text":"But the Jews that were at Shushan assembled together on the thirteenth day thereof, and on the fourteenth thereof; and on the fifteenth day of the same they rested, and made it a day of feasting and gladness.","ref":"Esther 9:18","synthesized":"The Jews in Susa, however, had assembled on the thirteenth and the fourteenth days of the month. So they rested on the fifteenth day, making it a day of feasting and joy.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"But the Jews that were at Shushan assembled together on the thirteenth day thereof, and on the fourteenth thereof; and on the fifteenth day of the same they rested, and made it a day of feasting and gladness."},"BSB":{"text":"The Jews in Susa, however, had assembled on the thirteenth and the fourteenth days of the month. So they rested on the fifteenth day, making it a day of feasting and joy."}},"definableWords":["days","day","joy"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"19":{"text":"Therefore the Jews of the villages, that dwelt in the unwalled towns, made the fourteenth day of the month Adar a day of gladness and feasting, and a good day, and of sending portions one to another.","ref":"Esther 9:19","synthesized":"This is why the rural Jews, who live in the villages, observe the fourteenth day of the month of Adar as a day of joy and feasting. It is a holiday for sending gifts to one another.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Therefore the Jews of the villages, that dwelt in the unwalled towns, made the fourteenth day of the month Adar a day of gladness and feasting, and a good day, and of sending portions one to another."},"BSB":{"text":"This is why the rural Jews, who live in the villages, observe the fourteenth day of the month of Adar as a day of joy and feasting. It is a holiday for sending gifts to one another."}},"definableWords":["live","day","joy","one"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"20":{"text":"And Mordecai wrote these things, and sent letters unto all the Jews that were in all the provinces of the king Ahasuerus, both nigh and far,","ref":"Esther 9:20","synthesized":"Mordecai recorded these events and sent letters to all the Jews in all the provinces of King Xerxes, both near and far,","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And Mordecai wrote these things, and sent letters unto all the Jews that were in all the provinces of the king Ahasuerus, both nigh and far,"},"BSB":{"text":"Mordecai recorded these events and sent letters to all the Jews in all the provinces of King Xerxes, both near and far,"}},"definableWords":["King"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"21":{"text":"To stablish this among them, that they should keep the fourteenth day of the month Adar, and the fifteenth day of the same, yearly,","ref":"Esther 9:21","synthesized":"to establish among them an annual celebration on the fourteenth and fifteenth days of the month of Adar","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"To stablish this among them, that they should keep the fourteenth day of the month Adar, and the fifteenth day of the same, yearly,"},"BSB":{"text":"to establish among them an annual celebration on the fourteenth and fifteenth days of the month of Adar"}},"definableWords":["days"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"22":{"text":"As the days wherein the Jews rested from their enemies, and the month which was turned unto them from sorrow to joy, and from mourning into a good day: that they should make them days of feasting and joy, and of sending portions one to another, and gifts to the poor.","ref":"Esther 9:22","synthesized":"as the days on which the Jews gained rest from their enemies and the month in which their sorrow turned to joy and their mourning into a holiday. He wrote that these were to be days of feasting and joy, of sending gifts to one another and to the poor.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"As the days wherein the Jews rested from their enemies, and the month which was turned unto them from sorrow to joy, and from mourning into a good day: that they should make them days of feasting and joy, and of sending portions one to another, and gifts to the poor."},"BSB":{"text":"as the days on which the Jews gained rest from their enemies and the month in which their sorrow turned to joy and their mourning into a holiday. He wrote that these were to be days of feasting and joy, of sending gifts to one another and to the poor."}},"definableWords":["days","rest","joy","one"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"23":{"text":"And the Jews undertook to do as they had begun, and as Mordecai had written unto them;","ref":"Esther 9:23","synthesized":"So the Jews agreed to continue the custom they had started, as Mordecai had written to them.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And the Jews undertook to do as they had begun, and as Mordecai had written unto them;"},"BSB":{"text":"So the Jews agreed to continue the custom they had started, as Mordecai had written to them."}},"definableWords":[],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"24":{"text":"Because Haman the son of Hammedatha, the Agagite, the enemy of all the Jews, had devised against the Jews to destroy them, and had cast Pur, that is, the lot, to consume them, and to destroy them;","ref":"Esther 9:24","synthesized":"For Haman son of Hammedatha, the Agagite, the enemy of all the Jews, had plotted against the Jews to destroy them and had cast the Pur (that is, the lot) to crush and destroy them.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Because Haman the son of Hammedatha, the Agagite, the enemy of all the Jews, had devised against the Jews to destroy them, and had cast Pur, that is, the lot, to consume them, and to destroy them;"},"BSB":{"text":"For Haman son of Hammedatha, the Agagite, the enemy of all the Jews, had plotted against the Jews to destroy them and had cast the Pur (that is, the lot) to crush and destroy them."}},"definableWords":["son","Lot"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"25":{"text":"But when Esther came before the king, he commanded by letters that his wicked device, which he devised against the Jews, should return upon his own head, and that he and his sons should be hanged on the gallows.","ref":"Esther 9:25","synthesized":"But when it came before the king, he commanded by letter that the wicked scheme which Haman had devised against the Jews should come back upon his own head, and that he and his sons should be hanged on the gallows.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"But when Esther came before the king, he commanded by letters that his wicked device, which he devised against the Jews, should return upon his own head, and that he and his sons should be hanged on the gallows."},"BSB":{"text":"But when it came before the king, he commanded by letter that the wicked scheme which Haman had devised against the Jews should come back upon his own head, and that he and his sons should be hanged on the gallows."}},"definableWords":["king","sons"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"26":{"text":"Wherefore they called these days Purim after the name of Pur. Therefore for all the words of this letter, and of that which they had seen concerning this matter, and which had come unto them,","ref":"Esther 9:26","synthesized":"Therefore these days are called Purim, from the word Pur.  Because of all the instructions in this letter, and because of all they had seen and experienced,","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Wherefore they called these days Purim after the name of Pur. Therefore for all the words of this letter, and of that which they had seen concerning this matter, and which had come unto them,"},"BSB":{"text":"Therefore these days are called Purim, from the word Pur.  Because of all the instructions in this letter, and because of all they had seen and experienced,"}},"definableWords":["days","word"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"27":{"text":"The Jews ordained, and took upon them, and upon their seed, and upon all such as joined themselves unto them, so as it should not fail, that they would keep these two days according to their writing, and according to their appointed time every year;","ref":"Esther 9:27","synthesized":"the Jews bound themselves to establish the custom that they and their descendants and all who join them should not fail to celebrate these two days at the appointed time each and every year, according to their regulation.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"The Jews ordained, and took upon them, and upon their seed, and upon all such as joined themselves unto them, so as it should not fail, that they would keep these two days according to their writing, and according to their appointed time every year;"},"BSB":{"text":"the Jews bound themselves to establish the custom that they and their descendants and all who join them should not fail to celebrate these two days at the appointed time each and every year, according to their regulation."}},"definableWords":["days","year"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"28":{"text":"And that these days should be remembered and kept throughout every generation, every family, every province, and every city; and that these days of Purim should not fail from among the Jews, nor the memorial of them perish from their seed.","ref":"Esther 9:28","synthesized":"These days should be remembered and celebrated by every generation, family, province, and city, so that these days of Purim should not fail to be observed among the Jews, nor should the memory of them fade from their descendants.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And that these days should be remembered and kept throughout every generation, every family, every province, and every city; and that these days of Purim should not fail from among the Jews, nor the memorial of them perish from their seed."},"BSB":{"text":"These days should be remembered and celebrated by every generation, family, province, and city, so that these days of Purim should not fail to be observed among the Jews, nor should the memory of them fade from their descendants."}},"definableWords":["days","remembered","family"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"29":{"text":"Then Esther the queen, the daughter of Abihail, and Mordecai the Jew, wrote with all authority, to confirm this second letter of Purim.","ref":"Esther 9:29","synthesized":"So Queen Esther daughter of Abihail, along with Mordecai the Jew, wrote with full authority to confirm this second letter concerning Purim.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"Then Esther the queen, the daughter of Abihail, and Mordecai the Jew, wrote with all authority, to confirm this second letter of Purim."},"BSB":{"text":"So Queen Esther daughter of Abihail, along with Mordecai the Jew, wrote with full authority to confirm this second letter concerning Purim."}},"definableWords":["daughter","Jew"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"30":{"text":"And he sent the letters unto all the Jews, to the hundred twenty and seven provinces of the kingdom of Ahasuerus, with words of peace and truth,","ref":"Esther 9:30","synthesized":"And Mordecai sent letters with words of peace and truth to all the Jews in the 127 provinces of the kingdom of Xerxes,","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And he sent the letters unto all the Jews, to the hundred twenty and seven provinces of the kingdom of Ahasuerus, with words of peace and truth,"},"BSB":{"text":"And Mordecai sent letters with words of peace and truth to all the Jews in the 127 provinces of the kingdom of Xerxes,"}},"definableWords":["peace","truth","kingdom"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"31":{"text":"To confirm these days of Purim in their times appointed, according as Mordecai the Jew and Esther the queen had enjoined them, and as they had decreed for themselves and for their seed, the matters of the fastings and their cry.","ref":"Esther 9:31","synthesized":"in order to confirm these days of Purim at their appointed time, just as Mordecai the Jew and Queen Esther had established them and had committed themselves and their descendants to the times of fasting and lamentation.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"To confirm these days of Purim in their times appointed, according as Mordecai the Jew and Esther the queen had enjoined them, and as they had decreed for themselves and for their seed, the matters of the fastings and their cry."},"BSB":{"text":"in order to confirm these days of Purim at their appointed time, just as Mordecai the Jew and Queen Esther had established them and had committed themselves and their descendants to the times of fasting and lamentation."}},"definableWords":["days","Jew"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"32":{"text":"And the decree of Esther confirmed these matters of Purim; and it was written in the book.","ref":"Esther 9:32","synthesized":"So Esther’s decree confirmed these regulations about Purim, which were written into the record.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And the decree of Esther confirmed these matters of Purim; and it was written in the book."},"BSB":{"text":"So Esther’s decree confirmed these regulations about Purim, which were written into the record."}},"definableWords":[],"peopleInVerse":[]}}},"10":{"chapter":"10","title":"MORDECAI EXALTED","verses":{"1":{"text":"And the king Ahasuerus laid a tribute upon the land, and upon the isles of the sea.","ref":"Esther 10:1","synthesized":"Now King Xerxes imposed tribute throughout the land, even to its farthest shores.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And the king Ahasuerus laid a tribute upon the land, and upon the isles of the sea."},"BSB":{"text":"Now King Xerxes imposed tribute throughout the land, even to its farthest shores."}},"definableWords":["King","land"],"peopleInVerse":[]},"2":{"text":"And all the acts of his power and of his might, and the declaration of the greatness of Mordecai, whereunto the king advanced him, are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Media and Persia?","ref":"Esther 10:2","synthesized":"And all of Mordecai’s powerful and magnificent accomplishments, together with the full account of the greatness to which the king had raised him, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Media and Persia?","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"And all the acts of his power and of his might, and the declaration of the greatness of Mordecai, whereunto the king advanced him, are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Media and Persia?"},"BSB":{"text":"And all of Mordecai’s powerful and magnificent accomplishments, together with the full account of the greatness to which the king had raised him, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Media and Persia?"}},"definableWords":["king","kings"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]},"3":{"text":"For Mordecai the Jew was next unto king Ahasuerus, and great among the Jews, and accepted of the multitude of his brethren, seeking the wealth of his people, and speaking peace to all his seed.","ref":"Esther 10:3","synthesized":"For Mordecai the Jew was second only to King Xerxes, preeminent among the Jews and highly favored by his many kinsmen, seeking the good of his people and speaking peace to all his countrymen.","sources":{"KJV":{"text":"For Mordecai the Jew was next unto king Ahasuerus, and great among the Jews, and accepted of the multitude of his brethren, seeking the wealth of his people, and speaking peace to all his seed."},"BSB":{"text":"For Mordecai the Jew was second only to King Xerxes, preeminent among the Jews and highly favored by his many kinsmen, seeking the good of his people and speaking peace to all his countrymen."}},"definableWords":["Jew","King","good","people","peace"],"peopleInVerse":["Mordecai"]}}}};